name: Book of Combos 1
description: An introductory text for first- time combiners. Improves your combination success rate.

name: Book of Combos 2
description: An entry-level text. Owning Book 1 and this improves your combination success rate.

name: Book of Combos 3
description: An intermediate text. Owning Books 1, 2, and this improves your combination success rate.

name: Book of Combos 4
description: An advanced text. Owning Books 1-3 and this improves your combination success rate.

name: Book of Combos 5
description: A pro-level text. Owning Books 1-4 and this improves your combination success rate.

name: Organizer Guide
description: An issue of "Hunting Life" magazine which tells how to maximize Item/Palico Boxes.

name: Pack Rat Guide
description: An issue of "Hunting Life" magazine containing advanced item-cramming techniques.

name: Binoculars
description: Allow you to see farther and observe from a distance.

name: Potion
description: Restores a small amount of Health.

name: Mega Potion
description: Restores a moderate amount of Health.

name: Nutrients
description: Very slightly increases your maximum Health level.

name: Mega Nutrients
description: Slightly increases your maximum Health level.

name: Antidote
description: Removes all traces of poison from your system.

name: Immunizer
description: Boosts your natural ability to heal.

name: Dash Juice
description: Lets you run without tiring for a short period of time.

name: Mega Dash Juice
description: Lets you run without tiring for longer than regular Dash Juice does.

name: Demondrug
description: Boosts your Attack by filling you with -- guess what? -- demonic strength.

name: Mega Demondrug
description: Boosts your Attack even more than a regular Demondrug.

name: Might Pill
description: Temporarily endows you with the strength of a mighty god. Potent!

name: Armorskin
description: Boosts your Defense by turning your skin as hard as rock.

name: Mega Armorskin
description: Boosts your Defense even more than a regular Armorskin.

name: Adamant Pill
description: Temporarily makes your skin as hard as adamant. Potent!

name: Cool Drink
description: Provides temporary relief from extreme heat.

name: Hot Drink
description: Provides temporary relief from extreme cold.

name: Cleanser
description: Immediately removes any ice or webbing on your body. Clean as a whistle!

name: Psychoserum
description: Temporarily sharpens your sixth sense and attunes you to the ways of monsters.

name: Herbal Medicine
description: Removes all traces of poison and restores a slight amount of Health.

name: Max Potion
description: Fully restores Health and maximizes the size of your Health Gauge.

name: Ancient Potion
description: Fully restores Health and maximizes the size of your Health and Stamina Gauges.

name: Energy Drink
description: A Guild-approved beverage that boosts your Stamina. Helps shake off sleep, too!

name: Lifepowder
description: Medicine made from compounded Lifecrystals. Heals those within range with a single touch.

name: Dust of Life
description: A medicine with strong curative properties. Studied in secret, it is said to restore youth.

name: Hunter's Drink
description: A beverage that temporarily makes it easier to fill the Hunter Arts Gauge.

name: Catalyst
description: Works with other materials to enhance their effects. Cannot be used by itself.

name: Gunpowder
description: A dangerous substance that explodes when struck or heated.

name: Lifecrystals
description: Mysterious crystals long worshipped as a source of life.

name: Tranquilizer
description: Medicine that works as an anesthetic when combined.

name: Yukumo Egg
description: A popular dish from Yukumo Village. Known for its rich yolk and how it melts in the mouth.

name: Tanzia Chips
description: A nutritious snack made with ingredients caught in Tanzian waters. Tastes like seafood.

name: Powercharm
description: An amulet that raises Attack. Just carrying this gives you demonic strength.

name: Powertalon
description: A powerful amulet that raises Attack. Made with a Deviljho Talon.

name: Armorcharm
description: An amulet that raises Defense. Just carrying this hardens your skin like stone.

name: Armortalon
description: A powerful amulet that raises Defense. Made with a Deviljho Talon.

name: BBQ Spit
description: Just what you need to cook meat. A must-have item for any hungry hunter.

name: Raw Meat
description: Meat carved from a monster. Can be cooked, combined, or used to set a trap.

name: Poisoned Meat
description: Raw Meat that poisons whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

name: Tinged Meat
description: Raw Meat that paralyzes whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

name: Drugged Meat
description: Raw Meat that puts whatever eats it to sleep. Makes great bait for traps.

name: Rare Steak
description: Provides a small boost to your Stamina. This one's still red in the middle.

name: Well-done Steak
description: Provides a moderate boost to your Stamina. Meat done right!

name: Burnt Meat
description: Meat that has been burnt to a crisp. It might boost your Stamina, or it might drain it...

name: Chilled Meat
description: Meat that cools the body, wards off heat, and restores a moderate amount of Stamina.

name: Hot Meat
description: Meat that warms the body, wards off the cold, and restores a moderate amount of Stamina.

name: Mosswine Jerky
description: Dried Mosswine meat. The more you chew it, the more flavorful and juicy it becomes.

name: Kingmeat
description: Like its name implies, it's the King of Meats. Doesn't get any juicier than this!

name: Whetstone
description: A standard-sized Whetstone. Use it to restore a weapon's Sharpness.

name: Old Pickaxe
description: A cheap pickaxe with an easily nicked blade.

name: Iron Pickaxe
description: A pickaxe with a reasonably strong blade.

name: Mega Pickaxe
description: A pickaxe tempered with steel. This one won't nick easily.

name: Old Bug Net
description: A cheap net for catching bugs. It tears easily.

name: Bug Net
description: A durable net for catching bugs.

name: Mega Bug Net
description: An extremely durable net for catching bugs. This one is made to last.

name: Boomerang
description: An unusually-shaped weapon from abroad that returns to its user when thrown.

name: Throwing Knife
description: A standard throwing knife. Flies straight and true. (Supply Item)

name: Poison Knife
description: A throwing knife with a venom- coated blade. Poisons targets. (Supply Item)

name: Sleep Knife
description: A throwing knife that has been dusted with sleeping agents. (Supply Item)

name: Paralysis Knife
description: A throwing knife coated with toxins that paralyze a target. (Supply Item)

name: Tranq Knife
description: A throwing knife used to capture monsters ensnared in traps. (Supply Item)

name: Bomb Casing
description: A base material for making hand-thrown bombs.

name: Paintball
description: Toss this scented paint at a monster to mark it, allowing you to track its position.

name: Flash Bomb
description: Flashes brightly on impact. Toss this right under a monster's nose to blind it.

name: Sonic Bomb
description: A grenade-like item that emits a high-frequency blast of sound on detonation.

name: Tranq Bomb
description: A hand grenade used to capture monsters ensnared in traps. Can be slammed against the ground.

name: Deodorant
description: An item that cures Stench. Releases a puff of deodorizing smoke when thrown down.

name: Smoke Bomb
description: Creates a large cloud of smoke wherever it lands.

name: Poison Smoke Bomb
description: Contains a toxic chemical. Also popular as a household bug bomb.

name: Farcaster
description: Instantly transports you back to base camp.

name: Dung Bomb
description: When thrown, releases a strong odor which certain monsters find repulsive.

name: Dung
description: That's right: monster poop. The odor reveals (too) much about the monster's diet.

name: Trap Tool
description: A must-have item for putting together Pitfall Traps and other kinds of traps.

name: Spider Web
description: A very sticky web.

name: Net
description: A sturdy net able to support a certain amount of weight without breaking.

name: Pitfall Trap
description: A trap for catching certain large monsters. It is tripped by a heavy weight.

name: Shock Trap
description: A trap that immobilizes a target. Use it to capture monsters.

name: Barrel Lid
description: A small barrel lid. There appears to be a drawing on it.

name: Small Barrel
description: A small, empty barrel.

name: Large Barrel
description: A large, empty barrel.

name: Barrel Bomb S
description: A small time bomb.

name: Barrel Bomb L
description: A powerful bomb triggered by external physical impact.

name: Barrel Bomb L+
description: Upgraded Large Barrel Bomb. Effective against large monsters.

name: Bounce Bomb
description: Launches into the air when set. This modified bomb requires skill to use.

name: Bounce Bomb+
description: An improved version of the Bounce Bomb. Requires some skill to use.

name: Affinity Oil
description: A red oil for the Sword & Shield. Once applied, it greatly increases Affinity.

name: Destroyer Oil
description: A green oil for the Sword and Shield. Makes it easier to stagger your target.

name: Stamina Oil
description: A blue oil for the Sword & Shield. Once applied, it will drain monsters' stamina.

name: Mind's Eye Oil
description: A white oil for the Sword & Shield. Once applied, your attacks cannot be deflected.

name: Huskberry
description: A berry that is hollow on the inside. Tough enough to grow just about anywhere.

name: Bone Husk
description: Used as a bone ammo casing. Produces sturdier results than a Huskberry.

name: Normal S Lv1
description: Ammo for novices. Cheap, but don't expect much. Unlimited shots.

name: Normal S Lv2
description: Non-specialized ammo. More powerful than Lv1. Capacity: 99

name: Normal S Lv3
description: Non-specialized ammo that ricochets, resulting in high damage. Capacity: 99

name: Pierce S Lv1
description: Armor-piercing ammo that deals multiple hits to some monsters. Capacity: 60

name: Pierce S Lv2
description: High-grade armor-piercing ammo. Deals more hits than Lv1. Capacity: 60

name: Pierce S Lv3
description: Max-grade armor-piercing ammo. Deals numerous hits. Capacity: 60

name: Pellet S Lv1
description: Ammo that covers a wide area. Deals multiple hits at close range. Capacity: 80

name: Pellet S Lv2
description: High-grade ammo that covers a wide area. Deals more hits than Lv1. Capacity: 70

name: Pellet S Lv3
description: Max-grade ammo that covers a wide area. Deals numerous hits. Capacity: 60

name: Crag S Lv1
description: Powerful ammo that lodges in a target and explodes. Also stuns. Capacity: 9

name: Crag S Lv2
description: Very powerful ammo that lodges in a target and explodes. Also stuns. Capacity: 9

name: Crag S Lv3
description: Extremely powerful ammo that lodges in a target and explodes. Also stuns. Capacity: 9

name: Clust S Lv1
description: Ammo that fragments into three shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire! Capacity: 3

name: Clust S Lv2
description: Ammo that fragments into four shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire! Capacity: 3

name: Clust S Lv3
description: Ammo that fragments into five shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire! Capacity: 3

name: Flaming S Lv1
description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Fire. Capacity: 60

name: Water S Lv1
description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Water. Capacity: 60

name: Thunder S Lv1
description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Thunder. Capacity: 60

name: Freeze S Lv1
description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Ice. Capacity: 60

name: Dragon S Lv1
description: Mysterious ammo that won't work in regular Bowguns. Capacity: 3

name: Poison S Lv1
description: Poisons target, but may require several shots. Capacity: 12

name: Poison S Lv2
description: Enhanced ammo that inflicts Poison. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 12

name: Para S Lv1
description: Ammo that causes Paralysis. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 12

name: Para S Lv2
description: Enhanced ammo that causes Paralysis. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 8

name: Sleep S Lv1
description: Ammo that induces Sleep. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 12

name: Sleep S Lv2
description: Enhanced ammo that induces Sleep. Some targets require multiple shots. Capacity: 8

name: Exhaust S Lv1
description: Special ammo that drains monsters' stamina. Capacity: 12

name: Exhaust S Lv2
description: Enhanced special ammo that drains monsters' stamina. Capacity: 8

name: Recover S Lv1
description: Ammo that restores a small amount of Health to an ally upon impact. Capacity: 12

name: Recover S Lv2
description: Ammo that restores a moderate amount of Health to an ally upon impact. Capacity: 12

name: Paint S
description: Ammo that marks a monster's position on your Map for a limited time. Capacity: 99

name: Tranq S
description: Bowgun ammo used to capture monsters ensnared in traps. Capacity: 8

name: Empty Phial
description: A regular old empty phial. Nothing more, nothing less.

name: Power Coating Lv1
description: An arrow coating that increases the Attack of arrows. Capacity: 50

name: Power Coating Lv2
description: An arrow coating that greatly increases the Attack of arrows. Capacity: 50

name: Elem Coating Lv1
description: An arrow coating that increases the elemental damage of arrows. Capacity: 20

name: Elem Coating Lv2
description: An arrow coating that greatly increases the elemental damage of arrows. Capacity: 20

name: C.Range Coating
description: An arrow coating that increases close-range power and melee Sharpness. Capacity: 20

name: Poison Coating
description: An arrow coating that applies Poison effects to arrows. Capacity: 20

name: Para Coating
description: An arrow coating that applies Paralysis effects to arrows. Capacity: 20

name: Sleep Coating
description: An arrow coating that applies Sleep effects to arrows. Capacity: 20

name: Exhaust Coating
description: An arrow coating that causes arrows to drain monsters' stamina. Capacity: 20

name: Blast Coating
description: An arrow coating that applies explosive powder to arrows. Capacity: 20

name: Paint Coating
description: An arrow coating that marks a monster's position on the Map for a limited time. Capacity: 99

name: Larval Extract
description: Highly aromatic, combine with Jelly or Ambrosia to create wholesome food for Kinsects.

name: Paralarval Extract
description: Highly fragrant, combine with Jelly or Ambrosia to make nutritious food for Kinsects.

name: Power Jelly
description: Tree sap loved by Kinsects. Perfect for growing strong and healthy Kinsects!

name: Heavy Jelly
description: Tree sap loved by Kinsects. Perfect for aiding robust Kinsect development!

name: Speed Jelly
description: Tree sap loved by Kinsects. Perfect for aiding rapid Kinsect development!

name: Fire Ambrosia
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; increases their Fire Element strength.

name: Water Ambrosia
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; increases their Water Element strength.

name: Thunder Ambrosia
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; increases their Thunder Element strength.

name: Ice Ambrosia
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; increases their Ice Element strength.

name: Dragon Ambrosia
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; increases their Dragon Element strength.

name: Power Jelly+
description: Thick tree sap loved by Kinsects. Perfect for growing strong and healthy Kinsects!

name: Heavy Jelly+
description: Thick tree sap loved by Kinsects. Perfect for aiding robust Kinsect development!

name: Speed Jelly+
description: Thick tree sap loved by Kinsects. Perfect for aiding rapid Kinsect development!

name: Power Jelly++
description: Very thick tree sap loved by Kinsects. Perfect for growing strong and healthy Kinsects!

name: Heavy Jelly++
description: Very thick tree sap loved by Kinsects. Perfect for aiding robust Kinsect development!

name: Speed Jelly++
description: Very thick tree sap loved by Kinsects. Perfect for aiding rapid Kinsect development!

name: Fire Ambrosia+
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; greatly increases Fire Element strength.

name: Water Ambrosia+
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; greatly increases Water Element strength.

name: Thunder Ambrosia+
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; greatly increases Thunder Element strength.

name: Ice Ambrosia+
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; greatly increases Ice Element strength.

name: Dragon Ambrosia+
description: A sweet nectar loved by Kinsects; greatly increases Dragon Element strength.

name: Douse Ambrosia
description: A sour nectar that reduces Fire Element strength and increases Dragon.

name: Drought Ambrosia
description: A sour nectar that reduces Water Element strength and increases Fire.

name: Resistor Ambrosia
description: A sour nectar that reduces Thunder Element strength and increases Water.

name: Melt Ambrosia
description: A sour nectar that reduces Ice Element strength and increases Thunder.

name: De-wyrm Ambrosia
description: A sour nectar that reduces Dragon Element strength and increases Ice.

name: Reverse Ambrosia
description: A nectar made by a Kinsect breeder; causes them to lose all of their Element strengths.

name: Alchemy Barrel
description: A hunting tool used by Alchemy Style Hunters. You can shake it to create new items.

name: Alchemy Food
description: Eat to restore some Stamina. It goes down a treat, but does leave you a bit thirsty.

name: Alchemy Immunizer
description: Eat this and your Health will gradually restore for a short time. It even smells healthy!

name: Alchemy Earplugs
description: These earplugs protect your delicate ears from loud monster roars...once. Talk about fragile.

name: Alchemy Slick
description: Crystallized Alchemy Barrel contents. Why not try combining it with other Alchemy Items?

name: Alchemy Cheer
description: Fills up some of your (and nearby allies') Arts Gauge and/or Support Gauge.

name: Alchemy Whetstone
description: Use this to restore your weapon's Sharpness and have your Arts Gauge fill faster for a while.

name: Alchemy Bullet
description: Alchemy-created ammo that fills your Arts Gauge faster (when it hits, that is). Capacity: 30

name: Alchemy Coating
description: Works with any Bow, and fills up your Arts Gauge a bit quicker. Capacity: 20

name: Alchemy Sonic Bomb
description: Launches a bird-like puppet that emits a screech that small monsters can't stand.

name: Alchemy Booster
description: This liquid of purest Alchemy allows your Alchemy Gauge to fill more quickly for a while.

name: Alchemy Fireball
description: This fireball blasts out of your Alchemy Barrel and explodes on impact.

name: Alchemy Remedy
description: Restores some Health and removes status afflictions from you and nearby allies.

name: Worm
description: A fishing lure. Wriggles underwater, enticing those fishies to bite.

name: Mega Fishing Fly
description: A fly lure that causes a feeding frenzy no matter what fish is biting.

name: Frog
description: A fishing lure. The ideal bait for certain aquatic monsters.

name: Sushifish Bait
description: A nugget-shaped fishing lure that makes Sushifish go "mmm."

name: Burst Bait
description: A fishing lure with chum that makes fish that rupture upon death go "mmm."

name: Goldenfish Bait
description: A nugget-shaped fishing lure that makes Goldenfish and Brocadefish go "mmm."

name: Field Horn
description: Used to attract certain monsters -- blow at your own risk. May break when used.

name: Health Flute
description: Restores Health to those who hear it. May break when used.

name: Antidote Flute
description: Eliminates poison in the blood of those who hear it. May break when used.

name: Demon Flute
description: Increases the strength of those who hear it. May break when used.

name: Armor Flute
description: Bolsters the defenses of those who hear it. May break when used.

name: Garbage
description: Junk created when a combination attempt fails.

name: Honey
description: Sweet, golden honey. High in nutritional value.

name: Herb
description: Restores a very small amount of Health. Not very flavorful.

name: Antidote Herb
description: A plant used in antidotes. It sometimes cures poison when eaten by itself.

name: Fire Herb
description: A wondrous, flammable plant.

name: Ivy
description: A lightweight and extremely strong plant.

name: Sleep Herb
description: A plant containing sleeping agents.

name: Sap Plant
description: A plant with leaves coated in sticky sap. Difficult to remove once attached.

name: Felvine
description: Melynxes' favorite food -- they just have to steal it.

name: Gloamgrass Root
description: Possesses antidotal agents, but it will not work by itself.

name: Hot Pepper
description: Blazingly spicy. Sure, it'll warm you up, but it's too hot to handle on its own.

name: Snow Herb
description: A radiant plant admired for the lovely white patterns on its leaves. It's as cold as ice.

name: Spicy Mushroom
description: A mushroom with bite that recovers a small amount of Stamina.

name: Frozen Berry
description: A completely frozen berry. Can provide relief from heat and recover Stamina.

name: King Cactus
description: The ultimate cactus plant, just touching its spines can put you in a world of hurt.

name: Dosbiscus
description: A large, beautifully colored flowering plant foreign to this land.

name: Heftcorn
description: Gigantic corn that's difficult to cultivate in this region. It's packed with kernels.

name: Stargazer Flower
description: A plant that looks to the heavens when it blooms. Its petals are used to make dye.

name: Prismatic Dandelion
description: A pretty dandelion with petals of various colors. It's used for making dyes.

name: Immaculate Ore
description: This piece of ore is small but somehow perfect. Used for forging and upgrading armor.

name: Dragonvine
description: Legend says that wherever an ancient dragon stepped, this vine grew. Used to make armor.

name: Tough Dragonvine
description: This high quality vine is said to grow where ancient dragons slept. Used to make armor.

name: Blue Mushroom
description: Rare mushroom with a power-enhancing effect.

name: Nitroshroom
description: A hard-to-find mushroom with the power to generate blazing heat.

name: Parashroom
description: A mushroom that induces paralysis.

name: Toadstool
description: Logic says not to eat this poisonous fungus, but don't write it off completely.

name: Mopeshroom
description: A mushroom that contains a Stamina-stealing constituent.

name: Exciteshroom
description: This one has a very strange aroma... But is it edible? Only one way to find out.

name: Dragon Toadstool
description: A dangerous fungus said to draw the life out of people. Beware.

name: Chaos Mushroom
description: A mushroom that invites disarray. Its spores cause monsters to hallucinate.

name: Bindshroom
description: A giant paralyzing mushroom. Just one touch can immobilize you, so handle with care!

name: Reststool
description: A large, poisonous mushroom. It looks like a comfy chair, but it's not worth the risk.

name: Paintberry
description: A berry with a shocking hue and an overwhelming scent. Look out: it WILL stain!

name: Might Seed
description: Temporarily raises your Attack when ingested by improving energy flow.

name: Adamant Seed
description: Temporarily raises your Defense when ingested by hardening tissue.

name: Nulberry
description: A mysterious berry that cures various Blights and also protects from unknown viruses.

name: Dragonfell Berry
description: A mysterious berry, rumored since ancient times to be loathed by dragons.

name: Scatternut
description: A nut that violently ejects its contents when struck.

name: Needleberry
description: A berry covered with needle- like thorns. Used as a material for ammo.

name: Latchberry
description: A berry with spiral grooves. It spins when it falls to firmly embed itself in soil.

name: Bomberry
description: A berry that explodes when struck.

name: Bumblepumpkin
description: A trendy orange pumpkin. If left undisturbed, it can grow to gigantic proportions.

name: Giant Acorn
description: An extremely large and firm acorn. The tree that it grows from is said to be gigantic.

name: Spiky Acorn
description: An acorn with a very sharp tip. It's especially hard before it turns ripe.

name: Yukumo Wood
description: A hearty tree that grows near Yukumo Village. It's pliable and easy to craft.

name: Yukumo Hardwood
description: A tree of high quality that grows near Yukumo Village. It's widely used as lumber.

name: Yukumo Stoutwood
description: A sturdy tree that grows near Yukumo Village. It's so rare, you can't buy the wood anywhere.

name: Stone
description: A small rock. Can be thrown.

name: Iron Ore
description: Ore that can be smelted into metal and used for many different purposes.

name: Earth Crystal
description: Crystallized microbes which are prized as an abrasive when forging weapons.

name: Machalite Ore
description: An ore that yields better metals than Iron Ore. Used to make Machalite.

name: Disc Stone
description: A disc-shaped stone. Not recommended to throw at your friends.

name: Ice Crystal
description: Ice that will not melt at room temperature. Can be used to create denser ore.

name: Bealite Ore
description: An ore that contains high amounts of gold. Can be used to create stronger metals.

name: Lightcrystal
description: An extremely hard substance with a faint glow. Sometimes used for crafting tools.

name: Dragonite Ore
description: An ore that yields metal superior to that of Machalite. Rare and valuable.

name: Firestone
description: Combusts even at room temperature. Its high heat can be used to fuse materials.

name: Allfire Stone
description: An ore that blazes with an all-consuming flame. Requires considerable skill to mine.

name: Lava Nugget
description: Melted rock stripped from the body of an Uragaan or Agnaktor. Various ores are mixed within.

name: Carbalite Ore
description: An ore still being researched. It yields even better metal than Dragonite.

name: Eltalite Ore
description: A promising new ore that produces higher quality metal than Carbalite Ore.

name: Meldspar Ore
description: An ore composed of a durable, flexible metal that works well as a combining agent.

name: Novacrystal
description: A brightly glowing crystal. Extremely hard, it's also used to make armory tools.

name: Purecrystal
description: A crystal that's 100% pure. Hard enough to be used in workshop tools.

name: Fucium Ore
description: Ore composed of a mysterious metal; capable of fusing nearly any two materials together.

name: Firecell Stone
description: A magma-like deposit that only trained hands can properly work with.

name: Rainbow Ore
description: A beautiful multi-colored ore. Colors and properties depend on many variables.

name: Pristine Ore
description: An exquisite ore sure to elicit a gasp from veteran smiths. Used for forging and upgrading armor.

name: Ultimas Crystal
description: A crystal used to reinforce metal. It improves both durability and shock absorbency.

name: Aquaglow Jewel
description: An indispensable item used in Decorations.

name: Sunspire Jewel
description: An indispensable item used in Decorations.

name: Bloodrun Jewel
description: An indispensable item used in Decorations. A shame that these are so high-end.

name: Lazurite Jewel
description: An indispensable item used in Decorations. This one doesn't come along often.

name: Adamant Orb
description: An indispensable item used in Decorations. A rare orb that houses immense power.

name: Sovereign Orb
description: An indispensable item used in Decorations. Rare and brimming with fierce power.

name: Armor Stone
description: Reacts uniquely to heat. Combine with other materials to create equipment coating.

name: Armor Sphere
description: Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse this to equipment to increase its strength.

name: Armor Sphere+
description: Fuse this high-quality Armor Sphere to existing equipment to increase its strength.

name: Adv Armor Sphere
description: A dense, rigid Armor Sphere. Rare, but enables higher- level equipment upgrades.

name: Hard Armor Sphere
description: A thick, dense Armor Sphere. Use this precious rarity to push equipment to the limit.

name: Heavy Armor Sphere
description: A thick, dense Armor Sphere. Use this precious rarity to push armor to the limit.

name: King Armor Sphere
description: A brightly glowing Armor Sphere. Use this scarce commodity to take your armor to new heights.

name: True Armor Sphere
description: An Armor Sphere of near-perfect purity. Its abilities require advanced techniques to extract.

name: Mystery Charm
description: A modest good luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

name: Shining Charm
description: A curious good luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

name: Timeworn Charm
description: A powerful good luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

name: Enduring Charm
description: A mysterious good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

name: Rustshard
description: Looks like a lump of dirt, but it's actually rusted metal. Try polishing it...

name: Ancient Shard
description: A fossil? No, it appears to be metal... With a little polish, it could be more.

name: Rare Fish
description: A lightly braised fish. Recovers the red portion of the Health Gauge when eaten.

name: Burnt Fish
description: A fish burnt to a crisp. Sometimes recovers Health, but can also cause harm...

name: Gourmet Fish
description: Recovers the red portion of the Health Gauge and increases natural recovery.

name: Whetfish
description: A fish with a dorsal fin hard enough to be used to sharpen weapons.

name: Sushifish
description: A fatty fish that can restore a small amount of Health. Helps cure Bleeding.

name: Sleepyfish
description: A fish that contains sleeping agents.

name: Pin Tuna
description: A fish with jaws covered in tiny, needle-like spikes.

name: Speartuna
description: A giant fish that's both rare and valuable. It looks like it could be used for something...

name: Popfish
description: A fish that literally pops when it dies.

name: Scatterfish
description: A fish that splits into little pieces when it dies.

name: Burst Arowana
description: A fish that bursts open when it dies.

name: Bomb Arowana
description: A fish that explodes when it dies.

name: Glutton Tuna
description: A fish that eats anything -- allowing you to sometimes get items from its stomach.

name: Gastronome Tuna
description: An enormous Glutton Tuna. Will eat anything, no matter the size.

name: Ancient Fish
description: A precious fish; almost every part can be used as material.

name: Small Goldenfish
description: A small, rare, gold fish. Commands a high price.

name: Wanchovy
description: A fish that can induce exhaustion.

name: Blue Cutthroat
description: A fish that emits blue light. Its sharp body will cut you to pieces if you're not careful.

name: Humspun Conch
description: A giant, spiked conch shell. If you listen closely, you can hear the melody of the tides within.

name: Armored Bream
description: A fish with massive scales, which have a wyvern-like quality to them.

name: Sharqskin
description: The skin of a carnivorous fish. Sought after for its unique feel and texture.

name: Springnight Carp
description: A species of carp whose arrival signals the start of the breeding season.

name: Tailed Frog
description: A rare frog that retained its tail. This only happens under special conditions.

name: Guardfish
description: An armored fish with a golden sheen. Sell it at a high price, or use it in crafting.

name: Insect Husk
description: The remains of a dead insect.

name: Godbug
description: An insect said to live for a thousand years.

name: Bitterbug
description: A sharp-tasting bug with innate healing abilities. Eat one for a 50% chance of curing Poison.

name: Flashbug
description: An insect that emits a powerful flash when it dies.

name: Thunderbug
description: An insect that emits electricity when struck. Has many applications.

name: Stinkhopper
description: A grasshopper with a foul odor. Make fishing lures with it; its scent drives explosive fish wild.

name: Snakebee Larva
description: An unusual larva to make fishing lures with; its scent drives the best fish wild.

name: Stygian Worm
description: Spins a jet-black silk which, when woven into cloth, can withstand wyvern claws.

name: Carpenterbug
description: Uses viscous fluids and sharp jaws to construct ant hills that are a sight to behold.

name: Shiny Beetle
description: An insect with dazzling wings. Its hard shell is often used as an abrasive.

name: Hercudrome
description: Said to be the world's strongest bug. Used in forging and other things.

name: Fulgurbug
description: Thunderbugs which have been stimulated by Zinogre. They emit a pale blue light.

name: King Scarab
description: The royal class of the scarabs, with a hard shell and lustrous wings.

name: Rare Scarab
description: A rare and valuable insect that greatly assists in the bonding of metals.

name: Blossom Cricket
description: A beautiful bell cricket resembling a flower. Its sound opens even the hardest of hearts.

name: Great Hornfly
description: An insect with a giant horn, massive shell, and wings of butterfly-like beauty.

name: Butterfly Beetle
description: A strange insect with the large jaws of a beetle and the delicate wings of a butterfly.

name: Great Ladybug
description: A giant insect with a very hard shell. Protects crops by eating harmful pests.

name: Emperor Hopper
description: A grasshopper with an exceptionally strong shell. Prized as a crafting material.

name: Flutterfly
description: A butterfly with shimmering wings. So rarely seen in the wild, many believe it to be a myth.

name: Toxic Kumori
description: An insect that possesses a powerful poison used by certain tribes for hunting.

name: Large Toxic Kumori
description: The largest of the Kumori, it possesses a deadly poison banned by many countries.

name: Lethal Kumori
description: An irregular Kumori that carries a fast-acting, lethal poison. You'd need a miracle to survive...

name: Dracophage Bug
description: It likes Dragonfell Berries, causing it to store Dragon Element energy in its body.

name: Monster Bone S
description: A very useful material; indispensable for both hunting and daily life.

name: Monster Bone M
description: A nicely-sized bone. Strong yet flexible, it's as reliable as steel and wood.

name: Monster Bone L
description: Wyvern bone needed to craft larger items. The right item will fuse this to a shell.

name: Mystery Bone
description: A weathered bone. Not sturdy enough to use for crafting.

name: Unknown Skull
description: Animal skull. So worn and weathered, its origin is unidentifiable.

name: Huge Unknown Skull
description: A large weather-worn skull of unknown origin. It looks strong enough to be used in crafting.

name: Monster Bone+
description: A high-quality monster bone. Hard to obtain, but vital for crafting powerful equipment.

name: Monster Keenbone
description: A rare bone with a razor- sharp tip that retains its strength even when crafted.

name: Monster Hardbone
description: A precious bone rarely yielded by large wyverns. Difficult to forge but prized for its strength.

name: Monster Toughbone
description: Arguably the strongest type of bone; it radiates an incredible strength and presence.

name: Monster Slogbone
description: An incredibly strong bone harvested from a fearsome wyvern. Its heft is impressive.

name: Elder Dragon Bone
description: A bone from an elder dragon. It exudes the great majesty of the beast.

name: Lrg ElderDragon Bone
description: Top-grade bone from a large wyvern. Its rough and majestic shape tells a vivid tale.

name: Avian Finebone
description: A bone from a Jaggi or other bird wyvern. Small in size, but high in quality.

name: Avian Stoutbone
description: The robust bone of a bird wyvern. Durable and easy to craft with.

name: Large Herbivore Bone
description: The thick, sturdy bone of a herbivore. Up there with the best of them.

name: Brute Bone
description: The stout bone of a brutish monster. An easy-to-work material.

name: Jumbo Bone
description: A large, thick bone. Often cut apart in workshops for use in crafting.

name: Stoutbone
description: The large, sturdy bone of a beast. Prized by blacksmiths as a prime forging material.

name: Massive Bone
description: An impossibly hard bone from a large beast. Exceeds all known standards for crafting material.

name: Dragonbone Relic
description: A curiously unfossilized bone from a dragon that once roamed these lands.

name: Dragonbone Artifact
description: Rare bone from an elder dragon that once ruled the land. A mysterious power lies within.

name: Irregular Bone
description: A bone with an unusual shape and color. It can be made into valuable equipment.

name: Irregular Stoutbone
description: An extra hard bone with an unusual shape and color. Used to create equipment.

name: Irregular Slogbone
description: A bone with an unusual shape and color. Its unusual sturdiness is used to forge strong armor.

name: Wyvern Fang
description: Used in Bowgun bullet points. Gunpowder shatters these, generating shrapnel.

name: Wyvern Claw
description: Used in Bowgun bullet points. Gunpowder triggers a blast with a wide radius.

name: Sharp Claw
description: A shining black claw. Unlike wyvern claws, this is shaped to grip objects.

name: Piercing Claw
description: Dangerous to touch with bare hands, it's used as a knife in some workshops.

name: Sharp Fang
description: Fangs come in many shapes and sizes -- the right fang for the right job.

name: Crushing Fang
description: Fangs come in many shapes and sizes -- the right fang for the right job.

name: Bird Wyvern Gem
description: A valuable gem that can be harvested from Jaggi and other bird wyverns.

name: Fey Wyvern Gem
description: An exceptionally pure gem taken from a bird wyvern. Its fragility makes it difficult to carve.

name: Wyvern Gem
description: Throughout a wyvern's life, impurities gather and form this peculiar gem.

name: Lrg Wyvern Gem
description: A Wyvern Gem grown especially large after years of collecting mass. Emits a peculiar glow.

name: Elder Dragon Blood
description: Contains an unknown ingredient, the object of much scholarly research.

name: Pure Dragon Blood
description: Elder dragon blood that contains a more potent mix of its mysterious ingredient.

name: Viscous Dragon Blood
description: Rare even among elder dragons, this mysterious blood has unknown potential.

name: Steel Egg
description: An egg of glittering steel. Very valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter...?

name: Silver Egg
description: An egg of glittering silver. Very valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter...?

name: Golden Egg
description: An egg of glittering gold. Insanely valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter...?

name: Platinum Egg
description: An egg of glittering platinum. Absurdly valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

name: Slickaxe
description: A small pickaxe that looks useless for mining. It seems to have a strange power...

name: Screamer Sac
description: A monster organ that emits an earsplitting sonic blast when ruptured.

name: Poison Sac
description: A monster organ that contains a lethal toxin. Handle with extreme care.

name: Toxin Sac
description: A monster organ filled with an extremely potent toxin. Just touching it is dangerous.

name: Deadly Poison Sac
description: A monster's internal organ filled with a most lethal toxin. Use extreme care!

name: Paralysis Sac
description: A monster organ that contains paralyzing neurotoxins.

name: Omniplegia Sac
description: A monster organ filled with potent neurotoxins. A single touch can cause Paralysis.

name: Ultraplegia Sac
description: A monster organ filled with highly concentrated neurotoxins. Handle with extreme care.

name: Sleep Sac
description: A monster organ that contains a knockout powder capable of inducing Sleep.

name: Coma Sac
description: A monster organ that contains dangerous powder. One whiff can induce a coma.

name: Torpor Sac
description: A monster organ that can subdue rampaging monsters in the blink of an eye.

name: Flame Sac
description: A monster organ filled with flammable powder. Handle with extreme care.

name: Inferno Sac
description: A monster organ filled with powder that ignites if it so much as touches air. Danger!

name: Conflagrant Sac
description: A monster organ filled with a highly explosive powder. Extremely dangerous!

name: Electro Sac
description: A monster organ that can store up electricity, which is released on impact.

name: Thunder Sac
description: A monster organ that can store up large amounts of high voltage electricity.

name: Lightning Sac
description: A monster organ that can store electricity as strong as lightning. Rumbles like thunder.

name: Freezer Sac
description: A monster organ with tremendous freezing power; turns its surroundings to ice.

name: Cryo Sac
description: A monster organ that has fierce freezing properties. It can coat an area in ice in a flash.

name: Aqua Sac
description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve water.

name: Torrent Sac
description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve copious amounts of water.

name: Flood Sac
description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve tremendous amounts of water.

name: Dash Extract
description: A mysterious substance culled from certain monsters that increases endurance.

name: Pale Extract
description: Has the ability to amplify the effects of certain medicines.

name: Hyper Extract
description: An unknown Extract taken from Hyper Monsters. Its details remain a mystery.

name: Potent Hyper Extract
description: A concentrated Extract taken from Hyper Monsters. Its details remain a mystery.

name: Hyper Fang
description: A fang from a Hyper Monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Fang+
description: An extra sharp fang from a Hyper Monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Hardfang
description: A highly dense fang from a Hyper Monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Keenfang
description: A sharp and weighty fang from a Hyper Monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Solidfang
description: An armor-plated fang from a Hyper Monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Claw
description: A claw from a Hyper Monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Claw+
description: A sharpened claw from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Heavyclaw
description: A highly dense claw from a Hyper Monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Keenclaw
description: A sharp and weighty claw from a Hyper Monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Solidclaw
description: An armor-plated claw from a Hyper Monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Monster Bone
description: A monster bone from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper MnstrToughbone
description: A monster bone from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper MnstrSlogbone
description: A monster bone from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely heavy.

name: Hyper Horn+
description: A sharpened horn from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Hardhorn
description: A sharpened horn from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Flame Sac
description: A flame sac from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Conflagrant Sac
description: A flame sac from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Pyroscale
description: A pyroscale from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Flarescale
description: A flarescale from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Aqua Sac
description: An aqua sac from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Flood Sac
description: A flood sac from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Fluid
description: A strange liquid from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Viscous Fluid
description: A strange, thick liquid from a Hyper monster, it's black and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Electro Sac
description: An electro sac from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Lightning Sac
description: A lightning sac from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Charged Shell
description: A charged shell from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Amped Shell
description: An amped shell from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Shockfur
description: Shockfur from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Fluxfur
description: Fluxfur from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Ice Block
description: An ice block from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Ice Chunk
description: An ice chunk from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Draco. Scale
description: A Dracophage scale from a Hyper Monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Draco. Scale+
description: A Dracophage scale from a Hyper Monster, it's black all over and extremely robust.

name: Hyper Toxin
description: Poison taken from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Potent Toxin
description: Potent poison taken from a Hyper monster, it's black and highly concentrated.

name: Hyper Paratoxin
description: Paralysis poison from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Potent Paratoxin
description: Paralysis poison from a Hyper monster, it's black and highly concentrated.

name: Hyper Sleep Sac
description: A sleep sac from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Coma Sac
description: A sleep sac from a Hyper monster, it's black all over and extremely durable.

name: Hyper Narcotoxin
description: Sleep poison from a Hyper monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Potent Narcotoxin
description: Sleep poison from a Hyper monster, it's black and highly concentrated.

name: Hyper Catalyst
description: Explosive liquid from a Hyper Monster, it's darker and stronger than normal.

name: Hyper Catalyst+
description: Explosive liquid from a Hyper Monster, it's black and highly concentrated.

name: Felyne Fur Ruby
description: A priceless ruby formed by the rare hardening of a Felyne hairball.

name: Larinoth Hide
description: The hide of the gigantic Larinoth. Its color is like fresh grass in springtime.

name: Larinoth Finehide
description: The hide of the gigantic Larinoth. Lauded for its beautiful hues and all-around toughness.

name: Gargwa Feather
description: A big, beautiful feather plucked from a Gargwa. Often used as a fashion accessory.

name: Gargwa Finefeather
description: A high quality feather plucked from a Gargwa. Stylish, and can be used to reinforce armor.

name: Moofah Horn
description: The horn of a Moofah. Since its shape varies by gender, it has a variety of uses.

name: Moofah Fleeceball
description: A fleeceball that's white and fluffy like a cloud. It makes supple yet strong thread.

name: Moofah Heavyhorn
description: The hefty horn of a Moofah. Resilient and easy to craft, it's a material with many uses.

name: Kelbi Horn
description: An infusion of powdered Kelbi Horn that works wonders on stomachaches.

name: Warm Pelt
description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

name: High-quality Pelt
description: Feels wonderful to the touch. Difficult to carve but valued by the Guild.

name: Prized Pelt
description: A quality pelt from a small animal. Often used in clothing for its comfort.

name: Anteka Antler
description: An antler often used as raw material for armor. Popular with interior decorators.

name: Anteka Proud Antler
description: A hefty antler that's valued by seasoned hunters and collectors alike.

name: Rhenoplos Shell
description: A shell that is very strong despite coming from such a small monster.

name: Rhenoplos Carapace
description: A carapace grown thick and hard over many years. Incredibly strong for a small-monster part.

name: Rhenoplos Scalp
description: A sturdy part of the skull that yields, shall we say, dashing results?

name: Slagtoth Hide+
description: Firm, lustrous hide often cut into large slabs. Prized for its water-resistant properties.

name: Supple Piel
description: A flexible, elastic hide from a leviathan. A useful material that requires effort to obtain.

name: Monster Fluid
description: A liquid bugs suck from monsters. Mixes with insect gastric fluids to form adhesive.

name: Monster Broth
description: A broth made from only the thickest of a monster's juices. Quite rich.

name: Monster Essence
description: A broth made from only the thickest, choicest parts of a monster's juices. Gross?

name: Bnahabra Shell
description: Just as useful as sturdy wyvern shell in the hands of a clever craftsman.

name: Bnahabra Carapace
description: The hardest part of the shell. Reveals curious properties when forged.

name: Bnahabra Wing
description: Difficult to forge with -- the results vary depending on which surface you use.

name: Bnahabra Razorwing
description: A wing that slices like a well-honed knife. Difficult to use in forging.

name: Altaroth Jaw
description: These durable mouthparts are surprisingly difficult to carve loose.

name: Altaroth Stomach
description: A transparent sac cut from an Altaroth's abdomen, used to store who knows what.

name: Quality Stomach
description: A high-quality sac cut from an Altaroth's abdomen. Its refined material is thin but durable.

name: Premium Stomach
description: A rare find, as Altaroth stomachs go. It can never be torn, or so they say.

name: Vespoid Shell
description: With special materials, it can be worked into very strong armor.

name: Vespoid Carapace
description: The hardest part of a Vespoid shell. Exhibits special properties when processed.

name: Vespoid Wing
description: Difficult to forge with -- the results vary depending on which surface you use.

name: Vespoid Innerwing
description: Blade-shaped innerwing of a Vespoid. The secret behind the beast's killing prowess.

name: Vespoid Razorwing
description: Much sharper than a Vespoid Innerwing. A simple graze is more than enough to cut.

name: Hornetaur Shell
description: With special materials, it can be worked into very strong armor.

name: Hornetaur Carapace
description: The hard part of a Hornetaur shell. Exhibits special properties when worked.

name: Hornetaur Wing
description: A hard-to-work material. Appears pearl-like when struck by light.

name: Hornetaur Innerwing
description: A blade-shaped innerwing of a Hornetaur. The secret to its killing prowess.

name: Hornetaur Razorwing
description: Much sharper than a Hornetaur Innerwing. A simple graze is more than enough to cut.

name: Hornetaur Head
description: With special materials, it can be worked into strong weapons or armor.

name: Konchu Shell
description: A shield-like insect shell as hard as any mineral. It emits an indescribable glow.

name: Konchu Carapace
description: A shield-like insect shell so hard that only a supreme craftsman can forge it.

name: Konchu Cortex
description: A shield-like insect shell so hard that only a supreme craftsman can forge it.

name: Shocking Extract
description: A concentrate of Thunderbug essence that releases an electrical discharge when struck.

name: Shocking Jelly
description: A gelatinous substance made from Great Thunderbugs. Easy to use and generates high voltage.

name: Remobra Hide
description: A glossy and subdued black hide taken from a Remobra.

name: Remobra Hide+
description: A lustrous and elegant black hide taken from a Remobra.

name: Remobra Finehide
description: The highest quality in Remobra skins. It shines with a luster reminiscent of a black pearl.

name: Striped Skin
description: Unassuming black-and-red hues from a Remobra that some hunters swear by.

name: Striped Finehide
description: Classy Remobra stripes on a resilient hide--a winner in any hunter's book.

name: Remobra Head
description: The snake-like head of a Remobra. It still looks ready to pounce!

name: Mighty Remobra Head
description: The snake-like head of a Remobra. Being in its presence may induce mild panic.

name: Bird Wyvern Fang
description: A sharp, durable fang from a bird wyvern. Used to make Bowgun ammo.

name: Maccao Scale
description: A scale carved from a Maccao. Although soft, it offers good protection from the elements.

name: Maccao Scale+
description: A superior scale from a Maccao. Its rigidity and durability make for excellent armor.

name: Maccao Shard
description: An especially tough scale carved from a Maccao that offers resistance to vicious attacks.

name: Maccao Hide
description: A Maccao hide stripped of its scales. Its elasticity allows for free and easy movement.

name: Great Maccao Scale
description: A scale that gets stronger when struck. Scales from the hands and feet are especially tough.

name: Great Maccao Scale+
description: A superior Great Maccao scale. The rarer, yellow scales are often used as decorations.

name: Great Maccao Shard
description: An especially thick Great Maccao scale that's become hardened over the years.

name: Great Maccao Hide
description: The braver the specimen, the duller and stronger this red hide becomes. Highly prized.

name: Great Maccao Hide+
description: Top-grade red Great Maccao hide. It is valued for its scars, and is used to reward valor.

name: Great Maccao Piel
description: The high quality hide of a Great Maccao, made resilient from old wounds.

name: Champion's Crest
description: Maccao males have decorative feathers, whose beauty is directly related to strength.

name: Glorious Crest
description: This eye-catching plumage indicates alpha status in the Great Maccao hierarchy.

name: Maccao Tailspike
description: Extremely hard, it provides balance, gripping the ground like claws.

name: Maccao Tailspear
description: A particularly hefty tailspike, even by Maccao standards. Indispensable for crafting.

name: Jaggi Scale
description: A scale carved from a Jaggi. Popular among hunters for its beauty and crafting versatility.

name: Jaggi Scale+
description: A vividly-colored superior Jaggi scale that can be used to produce hardier equipment.

name: Jaggi Shard
description: An excellent Jaggi scale favored by hunters as it can be easily worked into the toughest gear.

name: Jaggi Hide
description: Soft hide from beneath a Jaggi's scales. Cheap and easy to work with, it has numerous uses.

name: Jaggi Piel
description: Very thick, even for Jaggi hide. A distinctively smooth material that's easy to work with.

name: Velociprey Scale
description: A scale obtained by carving up a Velociprey. Blue and black in color.

name: Velociprey Scale+
description: A scale stripped from a Velociprey. It can be made into light, durable armor.

name: Velociprey Shard
description: A thick scale carved from a Velociprey. It's light and easy to carry, yet hardy.

name: Velociprey Hide
description: A hide stripped of its scales. Used to join the plates in a suit of armor.

name: Velociprey Hide+
description: The high-quality, descaled hide of a Velociprey, it has many applications.

name: Velocidrome Hide
description: The hide of a Velociprey leader. It bears the scars of a leadership role.

name: Velocidrome Hide+
description: Top-grade Velocidrome hide. It's extremely tough, despite being covered in scars.

name: Velocidrome Piel
description: Dense Velocidrome hide. It can take a lot of punishment, as evidenced by all the scars.

name: Velocidrome Claw
description: The claw of a Velocidrome. Its tip is as deadly as a sharpened knife.

name: Velocidrome Claw+
description: The sharp claw of a Velocidrome. It can easily slice through prey.

name: Velocidrome Talon
description: The sharpest of Velocidrome claws, allowing it to mercilessly rip its prey to shreds.

name: Velocidrome Head
description: A large head with a crest. You'd look pretty fierce if you put it on.

name: Genprey Fang
description: The poisonous fang of a Genprey. The paralyzing toxin works even on wyverns.

name: Genprey Scale
description: Scale from a Genprey. Acts as camouflage in desert areas.

name: Genprey Scale+
description: Scale taken from a Genprey. Strong enough to repel a wyvern's fangs.

name: Genprey Shard
description: Superior scale taken from a Genprey, that not even the sharpest of fangs can pierce.

name: Genprey Hide
description: A hide with all the scales removed. Can be tanned and turned into leather.

name: Genprey Hide+
description: The high-quality, descaled hide of a Genprey. It can neutralize neurotoxins.

name: Gendrome Hide
description: Sturdy green hide from a Gendrome. Perfect for making strong armor.

name: Gendrome Hide+
description: A high-quality green hide from a Gendrome. The hides of leaders are especially tough.

name: Gendrome Piel
description: Superior Gendrome hide, toughened by long years of leading the herd.

name: Gendrome Fang
description: The large and developed fang of a Gendrome. Be careful of its powerful neurotoxin.

name: Gendrome Fang+
description: The large and sharpened fang of a Gendrome. Its tip excretes a deadly neurotoxin.

name: Gendrome Hardfang
description: A mighty Gendrome fang, able to rend the flesh of prey and inject a vicious neurotoxin.

name: Gendrome Head
description: The head of a Gendrome. Noted for its two crests.

name: Ioprey Fang
description: A fang filled with deadly poison. Handle with care!

name: Ioprey Scale
description: Scale from an Ioprey. The poison irritates the skin so has been removed.

name: Ioprey Scale+
description: Superior scale from an Ioprey. Can be used in crafting once the poison has been removed.

name: Ioprey Shard
description: A massive poisonous scale from an Ioprey. Those who can work it safely are few and far between.

name: Ioprey Hide
description: Descaled hide, often made into belts. Red belts are used in decorations.

name: Ioprey Hide+
description: High-quality, descaled Ioprey hide. The red skin resists poison.

name: Iodrome Hide
description: A sturdy red hide from an Iodrome. Perfect for making strong armor.

name: Iodrome Hide+
description: Sturdy hide from the toughest Iodromes. It is very rare and hardly ever seen at market.

name: Iodrome Piel
description: High-grade Iodrome hide. Unbelievably strong, perfect for leading a large herd.

name: Iodrome Violet Scale
description: A violet scale carved from an Iodrome. It is more difficult to obtain than regular scales.

name: Iodrome Violet Scale+
description: A quality violet Iodrome scale. Its deep color borders on black--a sign of its quality.

name: Iodrome Violet Shard
description: An Iodrome scale of the highest caliber, proven by its deep hue, virtually black.

name: Iodrome Head
description: An Iodrome head with a large, eye-catching crest.

name: Giaprey Scale
description: A scale carved from a Giaprey. The color allows you to stalk prey in the snow undetected.

name: Giaprey Scale+
description: A high-quality scale carved from a Giaprey. Used to craft even better equipment.

name: Giaprey Shard
description: A superior scale carved from a Giaprey, used to forge high performance armor.

name: Giaprey Hide
description: Hide stripped of all its scales. Used to make clothing for villagers.

name: Giaprey Hide+
description: High quality hide carved from a Giaprey. Can be used to craft sturdy equipment.

name: Giadrome Hide+
description: Extra-high quality hide carved from a Giadrome. Often used to forge powerful armor.

name: Giadrome Piel
description: The best Giadrome hide one can find, used by any hunter wishing to survive the frozen wastes.

name: Giadrome Claw+
description: Sharp claw recovered from a Giadrome. Used for weaponry, but also for decoration.

name: Giadrome Talon
description: A thickened Giadrome claw. Keen-edged and able to cut like a blade.

name: Giadrome Head
description: Giadromes seem quite proud of their beautifully colored crests. Wouldn't you be?

name: Arzuros Pelt
description: A pelt carved from an Arzuros. The white portion is soft, while the blue is short and taut.

name: Arzuros Pelt+
description: A splendid Arzuros pelt. Sturdy enough to survive in harsh mountainous terrain.

name: Arzuros Fur
description: Exceptional Arzuros fur. Perfect for hunters to wrap up in, owing to it being both soft and tough.

name: Arzuros Shell
description: A shell piece from an Arzuros's head or back. Bends willingly and is easy to forge.

name: Arzuros Carapace
description: A quality Arzuros carapace. The thick shell can withstand bites from ordinary fangs.

name: Arzuros Cortex
description: A superior Arzuros cortex. This highly-developed shell is a huge thorn in all hunters' sides.

name: Arzuros Brace
description: A brace from an Arzuros's forelegs. Its sharp points give forged equipment a wild flavor.

name: Arzuros Brace+
description: A strong Arzuros brace. Its thorn-like protrusions make paw swipes deadly.

name: Arzuros Allbrace
description: A supreme brace found only on certain Arzuros. Its tough, thornlike protrusions silence foes.

name: Redhelm Pelt
description: A pelt hard enough to pierce flesh. Its looks embody the Redhelm Arzuros's brutality.

name: Redhelm Pelt+
description: A quality pelt that's hard and durable. Epitomizes the Redhelm's viciousness.

name: Redhelm Fur
description: The bristles in the Redhelm's fur show how shockingly ferocious it can be.

name: Redhelm Shell
description: A shell from a Redhelm Arzuros. Even its hard and sturdy shell looks fierce.

name: Redhelm Carapace
description: A superior Redhelm Arzuros scale. Even its thick and sturdy shell looks ferocious.

name: Redhelm Cortex
description: A superior Redhelm cortex. Extremely tough, evincing a ferocity that can dazzle the eye.

name: Redhelm Ragehair
description: The hair from the head of a Redhelm Arzuros. Its looks befit the beast's wild nature.

name: Redhelm Furyhair
description: High quality hair from the head of a Redhelm Arzuros that embodies its ferocity.

name: Redhelm Zenith Furyhair
description: Redhelm head hair of the highest quality. Extremely thick, showing off the creature's pure rage.

name: Lagombi Pelt
description: A white pelt carved from a Lagombi. One touch and you'll be hooked on its soft, fluffy fur.

name: Lagombi Pelt+
description: A quality white Lagombi pelt. Its glossy, frosty shine makes it a sought-after luxury item.

name: Lagombi Fur
description: The very finest Lagombi fur, durable and yet surprisingly soft. A top-shelf item.

name: Lagombi Ear
description: The long ear of a Lagombi. A lifetime in frigid environments has made it hard as a shell.

name: Lagombi Ear+
description: An impressive Lagombi ear. Highly developed, it can become sharp as steel if polished.

name: Lagombi Plastron
description: A shell piece from a Lagombi's belly. Its ridges are what allow the Lagombi to slide on ice.

name: Lagombi Plastron+
description: A strong, sticky, and thick Lagombi Plastron. Used to make superior equipment.

name: Lagombi Cuirass
description: Tougher and thicker even than Lagombi Plastrons, and glints from many ice-polishings.

name: Lagombi Iceclaw
description: A Lagombi claw that's cold to the touch. Permanently covered in ice from a frigid climate.

name: Lagombi Frozenclaw
description: A Lagombi claw surrounded by cold air. Wounds it causes freeze over in an instant.

name: Lagombi Frigidclaw
description: Fearsomely sharp and tough, even among Lagombi claws, able to tear up and freeze prey.

name: Snowbaron Pelt
description: A pelt that was carved from a Snowbaron Lagombi. It looks fluffy and is soft to the touch.

name: Snowbaron Pelt+
description: A hardened pelt taken from a Snowbaron Lagombi. Although stiff, it has a pleasing feel to it.

name: Snowbaron Fur
description: Particularly durable fur. The hairs feel wiry but the prickly sensation is actually quite comfortable.

name: Snowbaron Plastron
description: A shell piece from a Snowbaron Lagombi's belly. It is known for its deep ridges.

name: Snowbaron Plastron+
description: A high-quality Snowbaron Lagombi plastron. Its deep ridges give it a nice shape.

name: Snowbaron Cuirass
description: Even better than the Snowbaron Lagombi plastron, its pleasing shape approaches fine art.

name: Volvidon Shell
description: The heat-resistant shell of a Volvidon. Unaffected even by boiling lava.

name: Volvidon Carapace
description: A thick Volvidon carapace. Extra elasticity means extreme pressure is required to forge it.

name: Volvidon Cortex
description: A heavy Volvidon cortex. Difficult to forge with, but can produce very powerful gear.

name: Volvidon Claw
description: A claw from a Volvidon's forelegs. Dramatically increases the power of a wide swing.

name: Volvidon Claw+
description: A hard, sharp Volvidon claw. Constant exposure to heat has tempered it like steel.

name: Volvidon Talon
description: A punishing Volvidon claw. Its solidity and sharpness is almost overwhelming.

name: Volvi Rickrack
description: The jagged shell of a Volvidon's back. Its high elasticity makes it ideal for crafting flexible gear.

name: Large Volvi Rickrack
description: A larger variety of Volvidon shell. It combines flexibility and durability in one package.

name: Kut-Ku Scale
description: Pink scale from a Kut-Ku. Fire resistant. Can be found in the field.

name: Kut-Ku Scale+
description: Superior scale from a Kut-Ku. Its size and weight make it look classier than normal.

name: Kut-Ku Shard
description: A superb Kut-Ku scale. It's rare to see scales mature to this degree.

name: Kut-Ku Shell
description: The Fire-resistant shell of a Kut-Ku.

name: Kut-Ku Carapace
description: Harder than Kut-Ku Shell, this material is also known as Gravite.

name: Kut-Ku Cortex
description: A stout outer shell, much harder than a carapace. Also called Mediastinum.

name: Kut-Ku Ear
description: The Fire-resistant ear of a Kut-Ku. Used to prevent Bowguns backfiring.

name: Kut-Ku Auricle
description: A Kut-Ku's Fire-resistant ear. The flexible material is a good base for armor.

name: Kut-Ku Luckear
description: A full grown Kut-Ku ear. Considered a good luck charm due to its texture and form.

name: Giant Beak
description: The huge, sturdy beak of a Yian Kut-Ku.

name: Splendid Beak
description: Finding a large, beautiful beak in this condition is quite rare! Splendid!

name: Kut-Ku Webbing
description: Webbing from a Kut-Ku wing. Better than animal skin as a fusing material.

name: Kut-Ku Weave
description: Bulky webbing from a Kut-Ku wing, valued for its greater than normal powers of endurance.

name: Hyper Kut-Ku Scale
description: Darker than normal Kut-Ku scales, this Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Kut-Ku Shard
description: Darker than normal Kut-Ku scales, this tough Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Rubbery Hide
description: Highly elastic Gypceros hide. A good insulator, resistant to electricity.

name: Rubbery Hide+
description: High-quality, highly elastic Gypceros hide. Gives off a strange scent.

name: Rubbery Finehide
description: A special, highly elastic Gypceros hide. It absorbs any attack.

name: Gypceros Webbing
description: Webbing from a Gypceros wing. A good insulator, it is also resistant to poison.

name: Gypceros Weave
description: Bulky webbing from a Gypceros wing. Its improved insulation and toxin resistance make it valuable.

name: Gypceros Wing
description: A wing from a Gypceros. It is highly elastic and is a good insulator against electricity.

name: Gypceros Head
description: The uniquely shaped head of a Gypceros. A must have for Gypceros lovers!

name: Gypceros Hardhead
description: The hard, rubber-like head of a Gypceros. The rock-like noggin's popular among Gypceros fans.

name: Hyper Gypceros Hide
description: Darker than normal Gypceros hide, this Hyper hide emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Gypceros Piel
description: Darker than normal Gypceros hide, this hardy Hyper hide emits an ominous glow.

name: Azurefeather
description: The blue scalefeather of a Malfestio, the secret behind its silent flight.

name: Azurefeather+
description: A high-quality Malfestio scalefeather. Used in clothing as well as armor.

name: Azure Plume
description: A scalefeather only found on a small number of Malfestios. Shines with ethereal colors.

name: Malfestio Webbing
description: Webbing from a Malfestio wing. Its scales gather sound and emit a strange echo pattern.

name: Malfestio Wing
description: The deep blue wing of a Malfestio. Widely known for its beautiful curves.

name: Malfestio Grandwing
description: Malfestio wing with a refined curve, whose vivid blue color dazzles anyone who sees it.

name: Malfestio Wingtalon
description: A hard talon found at the end of a Malfestio wing. It's as sharp as a sword.

name: Malfestio Wingtalon+
description: A high-quality talon from a Malfestio wing. Hard and sharp, it's difficult to work with.

name: Malfestio Hrd Wingtalon
description: A high-quality talon from a Malfestio wing. Very hard and can be made exquisitely sharp.

name: Malfestio Ear
description: The ear of a Malfestio. Smooth to the touch, it's quite muscular due to its constant movement.

name: Malfestio Luckear
description: A big fleshy piece of Malfestio ear which has a multitude of uses.

name: Malfestio Tailfeather
description: The flamboyant tail feather of a Malfestio. Its color gradually changes from blue to gold.

name: Malfestio Tailblade
description: A high-quality tail feather taken from a Malfestio. As beautiful as it is dangerous.

name: Malfestio Goldfeather
description: The magnificent golden feather of a Malfestio. Collectors prize it for its sense of flair.

name: Malfestio Goldfeather+
description: A particularly high quality golden feather which enchants anyone who gazes upon it.

name: Hyper Azurefeather
description: Darker than normal Malfestio scalefeathers, it emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Azurefeather+
description: Darker than normal Malfestio scalefeathers, this tough Hyper feather emits an ominous glow.

name: Nightcloak Plume
description: A fine feather taken from a Nightcloak Malfestio. The color changes with viewing angle.

name: Nightcloak Grandwing
description: The plumage taken from a Nightcloak Malfestio is extra fine and deep in color.

name: Nightcloak Clearscale
description: Camouflages a Nightcloak in the wild, but weapons fashioned with them stand out in a crowd.

name: Garuga Scale
description: A scale carved from Yian Garuga. It shines an ominous purple.

name: Garuga Scale+
description: Superior Garuga scale. Looks like a Kut-Ku scale, but it's much tougher.

name: Garuga Shard
description: A top-grade Garuga scale. It sparkles like purple quartz and is just as hard.

name: Garuga Shell
description: A rare item, also in great demand as a research material.

name: Garuga Carapace
description: Garuga Shell that's become strong over the years. Great skill is needed to work it.

name: Garuga Cortex
description: A heavy, dark purple outer shell with an unusually intimidating air about it.

name: Garuga Ear
description: Its shape and form show a different evolutionary path than Yian Kut-Ku.

name: Garuga Auricle
description: Well-developed Garuga Ear. It's said to heighten one's senses when crafted into armor.

name: Sharpened Beak
description: The sharpened beak of a Yian Garuga. Looks fiercer than that of a Kut-Ku.

name: Rejuvenated Beak
description: A Yian Garuga beak. Its color, luster, and the jawline's angle have been restored.

name: Garuga Wing
description: A first class material that requires high crafting skills to work with.

name: Garuga Fellwing
description: A large, well-developed Garuga wing. It's highly sought after by crafters the world round.

name: Garuga Tail
description: The tail of a Yian Garuga. Responds to shocks by spouting a powerful venom.

name: Garuga Lash
description: A tough, hard tail that stores within a deadly poison that kills its target in seconds.

name: Garuga Mane
description: Mane from a Yian Garuga. Unusually intimidating.

name: Garuga Silverpelt
description: A shimmering silver pelt that mesmerizes all with its beauty when it flutters.

name: Hyper Garuga Scale
description: Darker than normal Garuga scales, this Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Garuga Shard
description: Darker than normal Garuga scales, this tough Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Deadeye Scale
description: A scale taken from a Deadeye Yian Garuga. Bears the scars of many hard-fought battles.

name: Deadeye Scale+
description: A hardened scale of a Deadeye Yian Garuga. Bears the scars of many hard-fought battles.

name: Deadeye Shard
description: The thick top shell of a Deadeye Yian Garuga. Bears the scars of many hard-fought battles.

name: Deadeye Shell
description: The shell of a Deadeye Yian Garuga. Bears the scars of many hard-fought battles.

name: Deadeye Carapace
description: A hardened shell of a Deadeye Yian Garuga. Bears the scars of many hard-fought battles.

name: Deadeye Cortex
description: A very hard Deadeye Yian Garuga shell. Bears the scars of many hard-fought battles.

name: Mosswine Hide
description: A musty hide covered in moss.

name: Mosswine Thick Hide
description: A thick, musty hide covered in moss.

name: Bullfango Pelt
description: A pelt from a Bullfango, covered in bristly fur.

name: Bullfango Pelt+
description: A high-quality pelt from a Bullfango. It's as tough as it is bristly.

name: Bullfango Thickfur
description: A top-quality pelt from a Bullfango. The fur is particularly dense and bristly.

name: Bullfango Head
description: A Bullfango head, complete with two splendid tusks.

name: Bulldrome Hide
description: The hide of a Bulldrome. Its bristliness has a certain beauty to it.

name: Bulldrome Hide+
description: The tough, unblemished hide of a Bulldrome.

name: Bulldrome Thickhide
description: The thick skin from a Bulldrome. It's too tough to get scratched through regular use.

name: Bulldrome Tusk
description: A majestic Bulldrome Tusk. The damaged surface tells the tale of many battles.

name: Bulldrome Tusk+
description: The large tusk of a majestic Bulldrome. It has been hardened through battle.

name: Bulldrome Hardtusk
description: The large, hard tusk of a majestic Bulldrome. Hardened through countless battles.

name: Conga Pelt+
description: The hard pelt of a Conga. The thick fur can be used to make long-lasting equipment.

name: Conga Fur
description: The hard fur of a Conga has to be sanitized before use, but its toughness is top notch.

name: Beastly Fang
description: A large fang from a Fanged Beast that can chomp the hardest of boulders in half.

name: Congalala Pelt+
description: The stout fur of a Congalala. Important crafting material.

name: Congalala Fur
description: The stout hairs of this pelt, coupled with its glossy coat make it highly valuable.

name: Congalala Fang
description: The fang of a Congalala. Solid enough to crunch objects into dust.

name: Congalala Claw+
description: A long, hard, sharp claw with a wild nature that makes crafting difficult.

name: Vibrant Pelt
description: Vibrant hair that grows on the head of a Congalala. The colors are lovely.

name: Vibrant Fur
description: The best vibrant hair from the head of a Congalala is beautiful and tough.

name: Congalala Hardclaw
description: Talons evolved specifically for combat. The natural weapon of Congalala.

name: Hyper Congalala Pelt+
description: Darker than normal Congalala fur, this Hyper fur emits an ominous glow.

name: Blango Pelt
description: A snow white Blango Pelt. It protects the body against the mountain cold.

name: Blango Pelt+
description: Keeps you toasty in frigid temps; harder to work with than normal Blango Pelts.

name: Blango Fur
description: This tough Blango fur is as beautiful as it is fascinating to craft items with.

name: Blangonga Pelt
description: White fur with astounding thermal properties and as strong as an iron chain.

name: Blangonga Pelt+
description: The hardened pelt of a Blangonga. The needle-like hairs are prized material.

name: Blangonga Fur
description: The tough fur of a Blangonga is harder than the depths of winter.

name: Blangonga Fang
description: The fang of the killer Blangonga. As sharp and deadly as a dagger.

name: Blangonga Fang+
description: A Blangonga dogtooth. As large as a human thigh, it has potential as a weapon.

name: Blangonga Hardfang
description: A Blangonga tooth that looks sharp enough to use as a skewer for cooking with.

name: Blangonga Whisker
description: A fine hair that sprouted from the face of a Blangonga troop leader.

name: Leather Beast Pelt
description: The fine tough skin of a Blangonga troop leader displays its authority and might.

name: Blangonga Tail
description: The smooth feeling of a Blangonga Tail is undeniably appealing.

name: Blangonga Lash
description: The tail of this Blangonga is silkier to the touch than fresh powder snow.

name: Hyper Blangonga Pelt
description: Darker than normal Blangonga pelt, this Hyper pelt emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Blangonga Pelt+
description: Darker than normal Blangonga pelt, this Hyper pelt emits an ominous glow.

name: Kecha Pelt+
description: A quality Kecha Wacha pelt that manages to be durable, yet still soft to the touch.

name: Kecha Fur
description: A fine Kecha Wacha pelt with a warm color and soft, sturdy coat. Very popular.

name: Kecha Grandbone
description: A quality, hardened arm bone that makes excellent armor in a gifted forger's hands.

name: Kecha Leadbone
description: A dense arm bone whose slender sturdiness makes it fine weapon material.

name: Kecha Talon
description: A thick, sharp talon that evolved for climbing up ivy.

name: Kecha Ripper
description: A unique hooked talon for crossing vines. Poses a threat in battle as well.

name: Kecha Ear+
description: The unmistakable, ocellated ear of a Kecha Wacha. Larger spots fetch a higher price.

name: Kecha Auricle
description: The unmistakable, ocellated ear of a Kecha Wacha. Larger spots fetch a higher price.

name: Kecha Tail
description: A tail with soft strands of hair. It feels wonderful to the touch.

name: Kecha Lash
description: A quality Kecha Wacha tail. Strong and supple, it may as well count as a third arm.

name: Hyper Kecha Pelt
description: Darker than normal Kecha pelt, this Hyper pelt emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Kecha Pelt+
description: Darker than normal Kecha pelt, this tough Hyper pelt emits an ominous glow.

name: Small Lobstershell
description: The shell from a King Lobster. A rare find.

name: Large Lobstershell
description: A large shell from a King Lobster that was used as bait. Very rare.

name: Giant Lobstershell
description: A large shell from a King Lobster that was used as bait. Very rare.

name: Cephalos Scale
