description: A sand wyvern scale. Its color is a brilliant blue. Retains moisture.

name: Cephalos Scale+
description: High-quality sand wyvern scale. It absorbs moisture, leaving it glowing blue.

name: Cephalos Shard
description: A thick scale packed with moisture, giving it a weird texture hunters go for.

name: Cephalos Fin
description: A sand wyvern fin. It isn't poisonous, but it's very sharp.

name: Cephalos Fin+
description: A quality fin that is sharper than other comparable samples.

name: Cephalos Grandfin
description: A high-quality Cephalos fin. Much sharper than your run-of-the-mill fin.

name: Cephalos Fang
description: The fang of a Cephalos, which are known for their rows of jagged and razor-sharp teeth.

name: Cephalos Fang+
description: A sharp row of teeth made for sinking deep into prey.

name: Cephalos Hardfang
description: An evolved fang. Strong and sharp enough to chew right through a Carapaceon.

name: Plesioth Scale+
description: A high-grade Plesioth scale with a lapis lazuli glow. It shines even when dry.

name: Plesioth Shard
description: A thick Plesioth scale with a lapis lazuli glow. It fends off claw and fang attacks.

name: Plesioth Fin+
description: A radiant Plesioth fin. Below the surface lie sharp barbs with a deadly neurotoxin.

name: Plesioth Grandfin
description: The finest and most lovely of all Plesioth fins. Produces top-class armor when forged.

name: Plesioth Fang+
description: A finely honed Plesioth Fang. Sharp enough to shatter the shells of small Carapaceons.

name: Plesioth Hardfang
description: A powerful, highly-developed Plesioth Fang. It can crush large Carapaceons with ease.

name: Plesioth Webbing
description: Difficult to forge with, but its water-retention properties make it popular as armor lining.

name: Hrd Ples Webbing
description: Stronger than normal webbing, and just as water-retentive. Ideal for lining armor.

name: Plesioth Head
description: A surprisingly hard head prized as armor material. Might make for a great party gag, too.

name: Uber Plesio Head
description: A frighteningly hard head found on a select few Plesioth. Among the very best in armor materials.

name: Hyper Plesioth Scale
description: Darker than normal Plesioth scales, this Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Plesioth Shard
description: Darker than normal Plesioth scales, this tough Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Lavasioth Scale+
description: A superior Lavasioth scale. The encrusted lava leaves behind a brilliant gold sheen.

name: Lavasioth Shard
description: A thick Lavasioth scale. Under the encrusted lava lies a golden treasure.

name: Lavasioth Carapace
description: Lavasioth carapace encrusted with rare hardened minerals, making for excellent armor.

name: Lavasioth Cortex
description: Heavy Lavasioth carapace covered in hardened minerals, making for excellent armor.

name: Lavasioth Fang+
description: A sharp fang from a Lavasioth. Its size is unusual for a Piscine Wyvern.

name: Lavasioth Hardfang
description: A hard, sharp Lavasioth fang. Its size is unusual for a Piscine Wyvern.

name: Lavasioth Fin+
description: A high-quality fin that has been sharpened into a virtual weapon due to the lava's heat.

name: Lavasioth Grandfin
description: A top-grade Lavasioth fin. The magma has endowed it with an extremely sharp edge.

name: Hyper Lavasioth Scale
description: Darker than normal Lavasioth scales, this Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Lavasioth Shard
description: Darker than normal Lavasioth scales, this tough Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hydro Hide
description: Hide that is highly resistant to Water. Don't expect it to sell for much.

name: Hydro Hide+
description: The durable hide of an aquatic monster. Highly Water-resistant, and in especially good shape.

name: Hydro Piel
description: This thick, durable hide of an aquatic monster is highly water-resistant.

name: Immature Sponge
description: A sponge from the sea that is not fully developed. Demand for it is high in general.

name: Spongy Hide
description: Hide that is highly resistant to Water. Don't expect it to sell for much.

name: Spongy Hide+
description: High-grade elastic hide that boasts a remarkable ability to retain water.

name: Spongy Piel
description: Nearly flawless elastic hide that retains water better than any comparable item.

name: R.Ludroth Scale
description: A small scale that enables graceful movement. Several are needed to forge equipment.

name: R.Ludroth Scale+
description: A large, strong scale from a Royal Ludroth. It reflects light in every direction.

name: R.Ludroth Shard
description: The ultimate Royal Ludroth scale. A rainbow of colors shimmer on its surface.

name: R.Ludroth Claw
description: A claw from a Royal Ludroth. Adapted better to movement than to attacking.

name: R.Ludroth Claw+
description: A sharp, pointed Royal Ludroth claw. It plunges deep into the earth with each step taken.

name: R.Ludroth Talon
description: A menacingly powerful Royal Ludroth claw that enables it to charge through any terrain.

name: R.Ludroth Crest
description: These crests become rigid when the beast is angry; quantity indicates status.

name: R.Ludroth Crest+
description: A proud, strong crest befitting a pack leader. Its sharp horns shine magnificently.

name: Chic Crest
description: A proud, strong crest befitting a pack leader. Its sharp horns shine magnificently.

name: R.Ludroth Tail
description: The finned tail of a Royal Ludroth, used by fishermen for their boats.

name: R.Ludroth Lash
description: A superior tail from a Royal Ludroth. Its strength shows it was honed in harsh conditions.

name: Hyper R.Ludroth Scale
description: Darker than normal R.Ludroth scales, this Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper R.Ludroth Shard
description: Darker than normal R.Ludroth scales, this tough Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Nibelsnarf Shell
description: A shell piece from a Nibelsnarf. Its great strength and hornlike bulges produce unique gear.

name: Nibel Carapace
description: A rigid Nibelsnarf carapace. Hard to forge, but the resulting equipment is worth the effort.

name: Nibelsnarf Cortex
description: A heavy Nibelsnarf cortex. Difficult to forge, but capable of producing impressive gear.

name: Nibelsnarf Hide
description: Hide from a Nibelsnarf. Many are surprised by its bright colors, in contrast to the outer shell.

name: Nibelsnarf Hide+
description: Quality Nibelsnarf hide often used as lining for armor. Strong enough to withstand the desert.

name: Nibelsnarf Piel
description: Honed by exposure to sand, this top-quality Nibelsnarf hide boasts great strength and elasticity.

name: Nibelsnarf Claw
description: Nibelsnarf claws have evolved to be able to quickly and easily burrow through desert sand.

name: Nibelsnarf Claw+
description: A bold, firm Nibelsnarf claw. Ideal as material for crafting superior equipment parts.

name: Nibelsnarf Talon
description: The sharp talon of a Nibelsnarf, perfectly adapted to burrow through sand. A quality item.

name: Nibelsnarf Scalp
description: A part of the skull that holds various organs. The useful bits must be cut out carefully.

name: Nibelsnarf Crown
description: The heavy scalp of a Nibelsnarf is difficult to work with but it's an extremely versatile material

name: Vivid Fluid
description: A fluid which helps retain water in a Nibelsnarf and allows the beast to thrive in the desert.

name: Brilliant Fluid
description: A fluid with strong water- retention ability. Improves equipment performance.

name: Dazzling Fluid
description: A sparkling fluid with impressive water-retention ability. Improves equipment performance and style.

name: Hyper Nibelsnarf Shell
description: Darker than normal Nibelsnarf shell, this Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Nibelsnarf Cortex
description: Darker than normal Nibelsnarf shell, this tough Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Lagiacrus Hide
description: Not especially durable, but soft and workable. Use it to forge valuable leatherware.

name: Lagiacrus Hide+
description: A fine hide taken from a Lagiacrus. It's quite strong and immensely flexible.

name: Lagiacrus Piel
description: The strong, flexible hide of a Lagiacrus. Used in expensive leatherwear, among other items.

name: Lagiacrus Scale
description: A supple scale that turns myriad shades of blue in the light. In high demand.

name: Lagiacrus Scale+
description: A fine example of a supple Lagiacrus Scale. Its beauty is truly breathtaking.

name: Lagiacrus Shard
description: The ultimate specimen of Lagiacrus Scale. Special skills are required to craft with it.

name: Shell Shocker
description: This shell is actually used to release electricity, not generate it. Safe to handle.

name: Shell Shocker+
description: A superior shell found only on certain Lagiacrus. Its structure permits greater electric output.

name: Deathly Shocker
description: A thick shell found on a select few Lagiacrus. It releases huge bolts of electricity.

name: Lagiacrus Horn
description: The power of Lagiacrus horns has been sung of for ages. In high demand.

name: Lagiacrus Horn+
description: A fine horn taken from a strong Lagiacrus. A horn like this is sure to catch people's attention.

name: Lagia Hardhorn
description: A fine horn from an especially strong Lagiacrus. So unique, it's almost legendary.

name: Lagiacrus Tail
description: Not only do these serve for weaponcraft, they also wind up on Moga dinner plates.

name: Lagiacrus Flail
description: Not only do these serve for weaponcraft, they also wind up on Moga dinner plates.

name: Lagiacrus Claw
description: A sharp claw that grows on the fin. Not pretty enough to command good money.

name: Lagiacrus Claw+
description: A very sharp claw found on certain Lagiacrus. Its mundane appearance belies its strength.

name: Lagiacrus Talon
description: A thick talon found on only a select few Lagiacrus. Adds both power and dignity to weapons.

name: Lagiacrus Plate
description: The largest and most prized of Lagiacrus scales. Boosts the efficacy of equipment.

name: Lagiacrus Sapphire
description: A gem only rarely plucked from a Lagiacrus. Craft with it to boost Resistances.

name: Lagiacrus Mantle
description: A valuable azure scale found on select Lagiacrus. Said to greatly boost equipment performance.

name: Hyper Lagiacrus Hide
description: Darker than normal Lagiacrus hide, this Hyper hide emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Lagiacrus Piel
description: Darker than normal Lagiacrus hide, this Hyper hide emits an ominous glow.

name: Uroktor Scale
description: A volcanic monster's scale. Highly resistant to Fire, but doesn't sell for much.

name: Uroktor Scale+
description: A high-quality Uroktor scale. Heat-resistant, bright crimson, and popular with the ladies.

name: Uroktor Shard
description: A superior-quality Uroktor scale. Heat-resistant, bright crimson, and popular with the ladies.

name: Agnaktor Scale
description: A scale so bright that it looks like it's on fire. Not worth very much, though.

name: Agnaktor Carapace
description: Sturdier and more heat-resistant than the Shell. It produces a vivid red color when crafted.

name: Agnaktor Cortex
description: The rigid cortex of an Agnaktor. Highly heat-resistant, creates bright red items when forged.

name: Agnaktor Hide+
description: Precious, high-quality Agnaktor hide tempered by frequent exposure to magma.

name: Agnaktor Piel
description: Top-quality Agnaktor hide with fantastic heat resistance. Thick but sufficiently supple.

name: Agnaktor Claw+
description: A claw sharpened by magma so hot it can melt rock. Almost as strong as a volcano itself.

name: Agnaktor Talon
description: A powerful talon found only on certain Agnaktor. Even magma cowers before it.

name: Agnaktor Fin+
description: An Agnaktor fin with an elegant dappled pattern. Apparently a popular item with collectors.

name: Agnaktor Grandfin
description: A premium fin lovely enough to have been painted by an artist. Behold the mystery of nature!

name: Agnaktor Beak
description: An Agnaktor's distinguishing beak, which allows it to tunnel beneath the earth.

name: Agnaktor Tail
description: A tail carved from an Agnaktor. The going price is low due to lack of demand.

name: Scalding Pleura+
description: A chestplate made from ore fusing together over a number of years. Won't melt, despite the heat.

name: Scorching Pleura
description: A burning chestplate tempered for ages. The various ores fused within are the key to its strength.

name: Hyper Agnaktor Shell
description: Darker than normal Agnaktor shell, this Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Agnaktor Cortex
description: Darker than normal Agnaktor shell, this tough Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Tetsucabra Scale
description: A scale with red and black patches that blends in well with cavern environments.

name: Tetsucabra Scale+
description: A fine red-and-black scale. The top pick for artisans who want the time-hardened best.

name: Tetsucabra Shard
description: A thick, red-and-black scale so hard that people justi- fiably mistake it for rock.

name: Tetsucabra Shell
description: A flexible yet hard rubber- like shell. In high demand as an armor forging material.

name: Tetsucabra Carapace
description: A flexible, highly durable shell that makes comfortable and easy-to-move-in armor.

name: Tetsucabra Cortex
description: Tough, rubbery plating that is difficult to break. A popular equipment material.

name: Tetsucabra Claw
description: A powerful claw that can pulverize rock. Short, but worth the effort to obtain.

name: Tetsucabra Claw+
description: A powerful claw that can pulverize rock. Creates scratch-proof equipment.

name: Tetsucabra Hardclaw
description: A powerful claw that can smash through boulders. Challenging to forge with.

name: Tetsucabra Tusks
description: A giant, shovel-like jaw, complete with tusks used for attacking and movement.

name: Tetsucabra Tusks+
description: A jaw with oversized tusks. Recent finds reveal damaged tusks grow back even harder.

name: Tetsucabra Gnawrl
description: A fang that grows like a mighty tree. Lost fangs are replaced by stronger ones.

name: Dignified Skull
description: A distinctly warped skull that is far more durable than normal bone.

name: Vicious Visage
description: A skull with opposing fangs and a sturdy lower jaw whose evolution warrants study.

name: Paddock Oil
description: A mysterious oil found only in nature. Used at the Smithy as a lubricant and additive.

name: Paddock Oil+
description: A mysterious oil found only in nature. Purer oil yields higher forge temperatures.

name: Paddock Cream
description: A mysterious oil found only in nature. Used at the Smithy as a lubricant and additive.

name: Hyper Tetsu. Scale
description: Darker than normal Tetsucabra scales, this Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Tetsu. Shard
description: Darker than normal Tetsucabra scales, this tough Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Drilltusk Scale
description: A Drilltusk Tetsucabra scale. It's hard and features a unique red and blue pattern.

name: Drilltusk Scale+
description: A hard scale of a Drilltusk Tetsucabra. It's sharp and features a unique pattern.

name: Drilltusk Shard
description: A thick scale of a Drilltusk Tetsucabra. Unbelievably hard with a unique pattern.

name: Drilltusk Shell
description: A Drilltusk Tetsucabra shell. It's quite hard and has a unique red and blue pattern.

name: Drilltusk Carapace
description: A Drilltusk Tetsucabra carapace. Its thickness makes it quite hard.

name: Drilltusk Cortex
description: An unbelievably tough Drilltusk Tetsucabra carapace with a unique pattern.

name: Drilltusk Tusk
description: The tusk of a Drilltusk Tetsucabra. Used to dig up large boulders.

name: Drilltusk Tusk+
description: A massive Drilltusk Tetsucabra tusk. An extension of its jaw and its brutality.

name: Drilltusk Gnawrl
description: A giant fang that is hard and sharp enough to grind a mountain to powder.

name: Sharqskin Scale
description: Zamite skin that feels smooth or coarse depending on which way you rub it.

name: Meaty Hide+
description: The hide from the underbelly of a Zamite. The most elastic samples are costly.

name: Zamtrios Hide+
description: A fine, stretchy hide. It tears only after new, harder skin has formed underneath.

name: Zamtrios Piel
description: A thick, elastic hide with high Ice resistance. Like wearing winter, yet warm.

name: Zamtrios Scale+
description: A fine scale that functions like sandpaper. Used to hone the edges of weapons.

name: Zamtrios Shard
description: One of many thick, razor- sharp scales that shred any foolish enough to touch.

name: Zamtrios Fin+
description: A quality dorsal fin that's in high demand. Big fins go for a premium at market.

name: Zamtrios Grandfin
description: A huge dorsal fin that cuts gracefully through the ice. Loved by artisans and hunters.

name: Zamtrios Sawtooth
description: A blunt tooth that slowly and painfully tears through the Zamtrios's prey.

name: Zamtrios Sawtooth+
description: Triangular, saw-like teeth for biting and crushing. Will grow back if pulled out.

name: Zamtrios Tailblade
description: A razor-sharp tail that does as well as any axe if one brings it down hard.

name: Zamtrios Tailbrand
description: A large tail whose meaty swings can knock prey out with a single lash.

name: Hyper Zamtrios Hide
description: Darker than normal Zamtrios hide, this Hyper hide emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Zamtrios Piel
description: Darker than normal Zamtrios hide, this tough Hyper hide emits an ominous glow.

name: Najarala Shell
description: A shell that grows both large and small -- whatever won't impede movement.

name: Najarala Ampsounder
description: A special plate that ampli- fies sound, getting messages across loud and clear.

name: Najarala Carapace
description: A long shell that covers the Najarala and may have evolved from a scale.

name: Najarala Cortex
description: The hardest part of the carapace. Multiple, layered plates provide durability.

name: Najarala Hide
description: Comparatively flexible hide found under the shell and on the underbelly.

name: Najarala Hide+
description: A fine, silky-smooth hide that sells well at market as a top-class material.

name: Najarala Piel
description: The finest of Najarala hides. Often used in all kinds of leatherwork.

name: Najarala Marrow
description: Marrow known to cause paralysis if handled improperly.

name: Najarala Medulla
description: A mass of tissue used as a coagulant in all manner of crafts.

name: Najarala Sounder
description: A Najarala shell with unique acoustic properties that amplify sound.

name: Najarala Sounder+
description: A shell with unique acoustic properties. Fragile and a real challenge to work with.

name: Najarala Fang
description: A fang containing an organ that induces neurogenic paralysis.

name: Chilling Beak
description: The Najarala's bird-like beak, which it uses to instantaneously seize prey.

name: Heart-stopping Beak
description: The Najarala's unique beak. Fangs inside it neutralize prey in ghastly fashion.

name: Hyper Najarala Shell
description: Darker than normal Najarala shell, this Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Najarala Cortex
description: Darker than normal Najarala shell, this tough Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Black Pearl
description: A pearl with a black glow. Fetches a high price.

name: Fine Black Pearl
description: Largest and most beautiful of all black pearls. Very valuable and hard to find.

name: Wyvern Scalp
description: A Carapaceon shell made from a wyvern's skull.

name: Heavy Wyvern Scalp
description: A Carapaceon shell made from a wyvern's skull that is harder than normal.

name: Decayed Crimson Horn
description: A red horn from a shelled monster. Despite the decay, it remains extremely durable.

name: Timeworn Crimson Horn
description: A faded horn which has been weathered over time but still has some value.

name: Sm. Hermitaur Shell
description: A piece of bone from a giant Carapaceon. Its small form means it has limited use.

name: Tiny Hermitaur Shell
description: A tiny piece of bone from a giant Carapaceon. It may be small but its value depends on its use.

name: Hermitaur Shell
description: A large piece of exoskeleton that's surprisingly light and easy to use in crafting.

name: Hermitaur Carapace
description: The hard carapace of a Daimyo Hermitaur. Harder than shell to work.

name: Hermitaur Cortex
description: A Daimyo Hermitaur's tough bone shell. Its thickness makes for strong armor.

name: Hermitaur Claw
description: A giant claw from a Daimyo Hermitaur. The sharp claw can slice through rock.

name: Hermitaur Claw+
description: Sharp claw from a Daimyo Hermitaur. As hard as metal.

name: Hermitaur Hardclaw
description: A Daimyo Hermitaur's hard claw. Tough enough to fortify castles.

name: Hyper Hermitaur Scale
description: Darker than normal Hermitaur scales, this Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Hermitaur Cortex
description: Darker than normal Hermitaur scales, this tough Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Stonefist Shell
description: The shell from a Stonefist Hermitaur. It has grown hard and dark over its many years.

name: Stonefist Carapace
description: A hardened Stonefist Hermitaur shell. It has grown hard and dark over its many years.

name: Stonefist Cortex
description: A very hard Stonefist Hermitaur shell. It has grown hard and dark over its many years.

name: Stonefist Claw
description: A claw taken from a Stonefist Hermitaur. It has grown hard and dark over its many years.

name: Stonefist Claw+
description: A sharp claw from a Stonefist Hermitaur. It has grown hard and dark over its many years.

name: Stonefist Talon
description: A very sharp Stonefist Hermitaur claw. It has grown hard and dark over its many years.

name: Small Ceanataur Shell
description: A piece of a giant Ceanataur Shell. Lighter than it looks and easy to craft.

name: Ceanataur Shell
description: A giant Shogun Ceanataur Shell. Has a distinctive color and shape.

name: Ceanataur Carapace
description: Harder than a Ceanataur Shell, this carapace is harder to work with.

name: Ceanataur Cortex
description: Thicker than normal Ceanataur bone, this high quality material demands a master craftsman.

name: Ceanataur Leg
description: A Shogun Ceanataur leg. Incredibly strong to support the beast's massive body.

name: Ceanataur Leg+
description: A giant Shogun Ceanataur leg. Extremely strong to support the beast's massive body.

name: Heavy Ceanataur Leg
description: An extremely thick Shogun Ceanataur leg. The shape is perfect for making weapons.

name: Ceanataur Claw
description: A giant Shogun Ceanataur claw. Those who fall in its path pay a dear price.

name: Ceanataur Claw+
description: The sharp claw of a giant Shogun Ceanataur. It's a true menace to hunters.

name: Ceanataur Hardclaw
description: A top quality claw from a giant Shogun Ceanataur. Reserved for use in the finest equipment.

name: Hyper Ceanataur Shell
description: Darker than normal Ceanataur shell, this Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Ceanataur Crtx
description: Darker than normal Ceanataur shell, this tough Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Heavy Rustrazor Scalp
description: A thick and durable skull bone from inside a Rustrazor Ceanataur.

name: Rustrazor Cortex
description: A thick and durable Rustrazor Ceanataur carapace used only by the finest craftsmen.

name: Rustrazor Hardclaw
description: A hard Rustrazor Ceanataur claw that possesses unrivaled beauty and toughness.

name: Nerscylla Carapace
description: A white shell popular with women and treated as a top- class material.

name: Nerscylla Cortex
description: Thick, opalescent plating with nary a scratch. Trades at an extremely high price.

name: Nerscylla Shear
description: A venomous fang that expands and contracts at will. Beware its lethal poison!

name: Nerscylla Scishorn
description: Stretching, poison-laden fangs found in a Nerscylla's mouth. Perfect for weapons.

name: Nerscylla Sharpclaw
description: One of the Nerscylla's sharp claws. Prey attacked by this never survives.

name: Nerscylla Hardclaw
description: An impressive specimen used once its web-weaving owner has danced prey in circles.

name: Nerscylla Spike+
description: A dorsal spike that is prized for its lethal poison sac more than its sharpness.

name: Nerscylla Surspike
description: Spikes from the back whose concentrated poison requires very careful handling.

name: Hyper Nerscylla Cortex
description: Darker than normal Nerscylla shell, this tough Hyper Shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Seltas Carapace
description: A hard piece of exoskeleton whose smooth surface reduces air resistance while flying.

name: Seltas Cortex
description: A thick but shockingly light piece of exoskeleton made of shock-resistant layers.

name: Seltas Innerwing
description: A vital organ for the flying Seltas. In high demand as a household material.

name: Seltas Razorwing
description: Fluid-filled wings that beat at high speeds to grant the Seltas flight.

name: Seltas Horn+
description: A sharp horn popular with artisans because, frankly, it's pretty deadly as is.

name: Seltas Hardhorn
description: A vicious horn that the Seltas sharpens on boulders as if whetting a blade.

name: S.Queen Carapace
description: A hard piece of exoskeleton that once made a Seltas Queen a veritable fortress.

name: S.Queen Cortex
description: An especially thick, iridescent carapace used in impressive Decorations.

name: S.Queen Hardpectus
description: A hard shell from the chest. Its non-slip surface exists so males can mount easily.

name: S.Queen Pectus+
description: Especially thick chest plating. Nearby gas holes have given it an odd aroma.

name: S.Queen Sharpclaw
description: A claw with a non-slip coating. Used mostly for movement and tunneling.

name: S.Queen Hardclaw
description: A beefy Seltas Queen claw. Dull, but its high durability suits it for equipment.

name: S.Queen Jaw
description: A shell that serves as the Seltas Queen's jaw. Used to expel potent breath.

name: S.Queen Maw
description: A large jaw that opens laterally to chew through meals with ease.

name: S.Queen Crescent
description: Moon-shaped shears that double as a tail. Used for defense when foes approach.

name: S.Queen Moonlash
description: Large shears from the tip of the tail. Inspires servitude from Seltas, fear in humans.

name: S.Queen Extract
description: A fluid that circulates through the body. Acidifies when it touches the air.

name: D.S.QueenConcentrate
description: An abnormally secreted substance acclaimed for its use in Neopteron forging.

name: Hyper S.Queen Shell
description: Darker than normal S.Queen shell, this Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper S.Queen Cortex
description: Darker than normal Seltas Queen shell, this tough Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Barroth Carapace
description: A Barroth's carapace coated in multiple layers of mud, making it quite rigid.

name: Barroth Cortex
description: A Barroth's cortex. Years' worth of mud have hardened it beyond all measure.

name: Barroth Ridge+
description: A thick, sturdy part of a Barroth backplate. Mud and sunlight have helped to harden it further.

name: Barroth Chine
description: The thickest part of a Barroth's backplate. Mud, sun, and age have made it rock-hard.

name: Barroth Claw+
description: A polished claw sharpened by sand and dirt. It can dig through even the toughest earth.

name: Barroth Talon
description: A strong claw found on only the most formidable of Barroth. It can easily dig through solid rock.

name: Barroth Scalp
description: This durable part of a Barroth's skull is also the hardest to remove.

name: Barroth Crown
description: The heavy scalp of a formidable Barroth. As hard to remove as it is durable.

name: Barroth Tail
description: Barroth tails aren't very valuable, but the meat is hailed as a delicacy.

name: Barroth Lash
description: A rigid tail carved from a select few Barroth. Inexpensive, but surprisingly versatile.

name: Fertile Mud
description: Mud that Barroth roll around in. Nutrient-rich and great for farming.

name: Hyper Barroth Cortex
description: Darker than normal Barroth shell, this tough Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Uragaan Scale
description: A hardened scale composed of ore that gives off a faint glow when exposed to light.

name: Uragaan Scale+
description: A strong scale formed by layers and layers of ore. Its hardness makes forging tricky.

name: Uragaan Shard
description: An impenetrable scale found on certain Uragaan. Formed when layers of hard ore bonded.

name: Uragaan Shell
description: This strong, sturdy piece of exoskeleton makes armor that looks dull but works great.

name: Uragaan Carapace
description: A hard Uragaan carapace. Its rigidity makes it quite a challenge to remove.

name: Uragaan Cortex
description: An especially hard Uragaan cortex. Crafting with it can be a trying task, to say the least.

name: Uragaan Jaw
description: A crooked Uragaan jaw. Coated with melted minerals that have hardened over time.

name: Uragaan Jaw+
description: An exceptionally heavy Uragaan jaw. Its destructive power comes from a makeup of dense ore.

name: Uragaan Scute
description: Even more heat resistant than the Shell, this is said to protect sensitive organs.

name: Uragaan Scute+
description: A highly heat-resistant Uragaan scute. Its thermal insulation promises new armor possibilities.

name: Uragaan Marrow
description: Hard-to-obtain bone marrow used for special crafts as well as medicinal purposes.

name: Uragaan Ruby
description: A precious Uragaan gem. Prized for its strengthening ability during the forging process.

name: Uragaan Pallium
description: A legendary Uragaan shell. Those who craft it rule the earth and seize the sky.

name: Hyper Uragaan Scale
description: Darker than normal Uragaan scales, this Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Uragaan Shard
description: Darker than normal Uragaan scales, this tough Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Crystalbeard Scale
description: A Crystalbeard Uragaan scale. Contains unique ores that make it shine bright.

name: Crystalbeard Scale+
description: A high-quality Crystalbeard Uragaan scale. Contains unique ores that make it shine bright.

name: Crystalbeard Shard
description: An exquisite Crystalbeard Uragaan scale. Has exceptional shock-absorbing ability.

name: Crystalbeard Jaw
description: The jaw from a Crystalbeard Uragaan. Contains unique ores that make it shine bright.

name: Crystalbeard Maw
description: A high-quality Crystalbeard Uragaan jaw. Contains unique ores that make it shine bright.

name: Crystalbeard Mandible
description: An exceptional Crystalbeard Uragaan jaw. Contains so much ore that it is dazzlingly bright.

name: Treasure Nugget
description: A stone shard taken from a Crystalbeard Uragaan. Prized for the rare minerals within it.

name: Large Treasure Nugget
description: A large stone shard taken from a Crystalbeard Uragaan. Prized for the rare minerals within it.

name: Brach Shell
description: A dark green Brachydios shell. Glossy like obsidian, it adds a refined beauty to crafted gear.

name: Brach Carapace
description: A hard Brachydios carapace. Glossy like obsidian, it adds a refined beauty to crafted gear.

name: Brach Cortex
description: Thick cortex of a Brachydios. Its stoic beauty adds strength and dignity to equipment.

name: Brach Ebonshell
description: An obsidian Brachydios brace. Makes especially strong armor, perhaps due to the slime mold.

name: Brach Ebonshell+
description: An obsidian shell from the foreleg. It has evolved to withstand slime blasts.

name: Fine Brach Ebonshell
description: A premium Brachydios brace. The slime coating may contain weird bacteria, so be careful.

name: Brach Scalp
description: The large, protruding scalp of a Brachydios, covered in an explosive green substance.

name: Brach Scalp+
description: A hard and sharp scalp piece from a fierce Brachydios. Even more explosive than usual.

name: Brach Crown
description: A large head projection that continually produces potent slime from within.

name: Brach Warhead
description: A skull that rage has turned into something far worse. The pinnacle of materials.

name: Mystery Slime
description: The explosive green substance found on Brachydios monsters. Handle with extreme care.

name: Glowing Slime
description: A highly volatile fluid used by especially savage Brachydios. Handle very carefully!

name: Flashpoint Slime
description: Red Brachydios slime at its most volatile: right before an all-or-nothing attack.

name: Brach Hammer
description: An arm that has crushed the courage out of many a hunter. Slime makes forging tricky.

name: Brach Pounder
description: A Brachydios arm that buried countless foolhardy hunters. It's covered in green slime.

name: Brach Pounder+
description: The arm of an especially angry Brachydios. Strong and heavy, as if made of iron.

name: Brach Obliterator
description: A violent mass that triggers blasts well beyond anything a Barrel Bomb L can do.

name: Brach Tail
description: While most focus on Brachydios's arms, its tail is also strong. Beware the explosive slime!

name: Brach Lash
description: A strong tail that hits like a cudgel and smashes through boulders like so much dust.

name: Brach Marrow
description: Stickier than normal marrow. A top-class welding material, if you're in the market.

name: Brach Gem
description: A rare gem from a Brachydios. Perhaps the secret of its dreadful slime is hidden inside?

name: Brach Pallium
description: A legendary Brachydios shell. Those who craft it rule the earth and seize the sky.

name: Immortal Reactor
description: A hard-to-obtain Brachydios organ. Used to render slime more volatile when in peril.

name: Hyper Brach Shell
description: Darker than normal Brachydios shell, this Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Brach Cortex
description: Darker than normal Brachydios shell, this tough Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Duram Carapace
description: A stiff Duramboros carapace. It can withstand attacks like an impenetrable aegis.

name: Duramboros Cortex
description: A Duramboros cortex. This heavy, strong armor saps an opponent's will to fight.

name: Hard Mossplate
description: A shell covered in moss. Not only is it hard, the moss absorbs the shock of physical blows.

name: Heavy Mossplate
description: A Duramboros cortex covered in moss. Its weight and mossy shock absorber make it impenetrable.

name: Duramboros Hump
description: The hump of a Duramboros's back. The fatty skin produces sturdy, pliable equipment when crafted.

name: Marbled Hump
description: A quality hump found on select Duramboros. Currently being researched as a possible delicacy.

name: Duram Tailcase+
description: A superior Duramboros tailcase. Slices and crushes using sharp shell and heavy bone.

name: Duram Hardtail
description: A rigid shell from a Duramboros's tail. Powerful and heavy enough to smash through mountains.

name: Duramboros Horn+
description: A rigid Duramboros horn. Nothing in the world can stop it during a vicious charge.

name: Duramboros Hardhorn
description: An incredibly hard Duramboros horn that somehow manages to amplify the monster's ferocity.

name: Duram Sacrum
description: A striking Duramboros sacrum. Such tough, symmetrical bones are considered rare materials.

name: Durambolite
description: Legendary gem rarely produced inside a Duramboros's body. Elegant, though gloomy.

name: Hyper Duram Shell
description: Darker than normal Duramboros shell, this Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Duram Cortex
description: Darker than normal Duramboros shell, this tough Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Flabby Hide
description: Finally useable as a material thanks to recent advances. Has mysterious properties.

name: Pearl Hide
description: The hide of a Khezu. Its strange properties are still not fully understood.

name: Pearl Glosshide
description: Top-quality Khezu hide. Hunters must take caution not to be enraptured by its luster.

name: Pale Bone
description: The rib bone from a Khezu. Still has chunks of meat attached.

name: Pale Steak
description: Fatty meat from a Khezu. Looks tasty, but cannot be eaten.

name: Khezu Special Cut
description: An extremely high-quality cut of red Khezu flesh. ...Yuck.

name: Hyper Khezu Hide
description: Darker than normal Khezu hide, this Hyper hide emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Khezu Glosshide
description: Darker than normal Khezu hide, this tough Hyper hide emits an ominous glow.

name: Nargacuga Scale
description: A scale from a Nargacuga. The surface is covered with the beast's black fur.

name: Nargacuga Scale+
description: A black Nargacuga scale. Despite its hardness, it's surprisingly light and smooth.

name: Nargacuga Shard
description: A tough, black Nargacuga scale. Thicker than standard scales, but still lightweight.

name: Nargacuga Blackfur
description: Black fur that grows on scales. Covers the animal in jet-black darkness.

name: Nargacuga Pelt+
description: Pitch-black fur from a Nargacuga. It absorbs all light and emits pure darkness.

name: Nargacuga Blackfur+
description: A Nargacuga's highly evolved black fur. Glossy and resilient, it fends off claws and fangs.

name: Nargacuga Tail
description: A Nargacuga's impressive tail. Might be mistaken for a weapon if seen out of context.

name: Hyper Narga Shard

name: Silverwind Blackpelage

name: Barioth Carapace

name: Dreadqueen Shard

name: Rathalos Plate
description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.

name: Rathalos Ruby

name: Hyper Zinogre Cortex
description: Darker than normal Zinogre shell, this tough Hyper shell emits an ominous glow.

name: Thunderlord Gleamhorn

name: Astalos Scale

description: The spiny shell of an Astalos that covers it like armor. Try to keep a safe distance!

name: Boltscale

name: Astalos Mantle

name: Boltreaver Electric Barb
description: A Boltreaver Astalos barb that can withstand immense electrical currents.

name: Gammoth Pelt

name: Gammoth Cortex

name: Gammoth Fang
description: A large fang taken from a Gammoth. Valued for being tough, yet still pliable.

name: Gammoth Fang+
description: An extremely hard and tough Gammoth fang. Difficult to work with, but versatile.

name: Gammoth Hardfang

name: Hyper Gammoth Fur X

name: Elderfrost Pelt

name: Elderfrost Cortex
description: This Elderfrost Gammoth shell won't let anything or anyone near you. Peerless strength.

name: Elderfrost Trunkspine

name: Mizutsune Scale

name: Mizutsune Shard

name: Mizutsune Purplefur

name: Mizutsune Purplefur+

name: Purple Mizutsune Tail

description: The top layer of a Mizutsune's fluid. It removes impurities and is used in religious rituals.

name: Distilled Bubblefoam
description: The top layer of a Mizutsune's fluid, strained and distilled to the highest purity.

name: Mizutsune Plate

name: Mizutsune Water Orb

name: Mizutsune Pallium
description: A legendary Mizutsune scale. Those who craft it rule the earth and seize the sky.

name: Hyper Mizutsune Scale
description: Darker than normal Mizutsune scales, this Hyper scale emits an ominous glow.

name: Hyper Mizutsune Scale X
description: Darker than normal Mizutsune scales, this Hyper scale emits a steady, ominous glow.

name: Soulseer Shard

name: Soulseer Purplehide
description: A beautiful Soulseer Mizutsune pelt. One stroke of its soft fur is enough to bring calm.

name: Soulseer Tail
description: Those who touch this Soulseer Mizutsune tail are captivated by its loveliness. A priceless article.

name: Glavenus Scale
description: A Glavenus scale. Along with the shell, they cover its body's vulnerable parts.

name: Glavenus Scale+
description: A quality scale taken from a Glavenus. It possesses excellent heat and damage resistance.

name: Glavenus Shard
description: A Glavenus scale whose heat resistance and protection could probably withstand hellfire.

name: Glavenus Shell
description: A shell covering the entire body of a Glavenus. It easily deflects all but the strongest blows.

name: Glavenus Carapace

name: Glavenus Cortex
description: The tough shell of a Glavenus. When forged to its limit, it makes completely impenetrable armor.
